om, Facility Visit Ubud Coffee Plantation Bali Coffee Plantation is a green garden for cultivating coffee from various types of coffee in the world. You can find the various of coffee plantation in this garden. In fact, you can also find other plants such as cocoa, coconut or other tropical plants such as medicinal plants or herbs. Furthermore, Indonesia is one of the best coffee producing countries. Even, the annual production of 600 thousand tons can supply seven percent of the world’s coffee needs. There are different things that you will find at Bali Coffee Plantations, namely Luwak Coffee. This type of coffee is very well known as well as the most expensive coffee in the world. This coffee comes from civet droppings that have been processed in such a way. Continue to visit Ubud Royal Palace Puri Saren Ubud or more popular name as a Bali Ubud Royal Palace is an Ubud Kingdom Palace with Beautiful Balinese traditional houses of residence of Ubud King. It is set in the center of Ubud Bali with traditional art market just in front of it and it is found by IDA Tjokorda Putu Kandel who has commanded from Year 1800 – 1823. If time permits, we can drop by Ubud Art Market. The Ubud Art Market is a great place to find beautiful silk scarves, lightweight shirts, statues, kites, handmade woven bags, baskets or hats and many other hand – crafted goods. Locally known as Pasar Seni Ubud, the market is opposite the Puri Saren Royal Ubud Palace and opens daily. Overnight stay at Kuta., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa Beach with Uluwatu Temple Tour Followed with Kecak Dance. (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Salty Air! Sandy Hair! Feel the tropical breeze and get closer to Indian Ocean with our selected Water Sports Activity. Pick up for Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa Beach (Incl. 1 x Jet Ski – Banana Boat Ride) and Complimentary 1 x Parasailing or Flying Fish. Later proceed Uluwatu Temple sits on 70-meter-high cliff protruding above Indonesian Ocean. The main site of Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkey’s dwells here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influence. The Serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff sides. When sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’. Kecak dance is that the accompanying music is provided by the human voice, the gamelan suara, a choir of a hundred men or more sitting in concentric circle, swaying, standing up, lying prone as the story develops. Amongst the swaying masses the voices of the storytellers can be heard telling the unfolding tale. The music generated from a combination sounds of members cak which were about 50 – 70 people all of them will make music in acapella. Overnight stay at Villa., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Day free for Leisure Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Today Day is at leisure to explore Bali or shopping at the local market. Overnight stay at Villa., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Depart from Kuta Morning after breakfast; you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back home to India. * The above itinerary is tentative and subject to change without prior notice. EXTENSION NIGHTS KUTA: Travel Validity: 01 Oct – 20 Dec 2024 & 07 Jan – 31 Mar 2025 CATEGORY HOTELS PACKAGE COST: PER PERSON IN USD SINGLE TWIN /DOUBLE TRIPLE CHILDWITH BED CHILD NO BED STANDARD Hotel Siesta Legian (Superior Room) or similar NA 32 NA NA NA VALUE Antanya Hotel Kuta (Deluxe Room) /Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar NA 50 NA NA NA EXTENSION NIGHTS VILLA: Travel Validity: 01 Oct – 20 Dec 2024 & 07 Jan – 31 Mar 2025 CATEGORY HOTELS PACKAGE COST: PER PERSON IN USD SINGLE TWIN /DOUBLE TRIPLE CHILDWITH BED CHILD NO B