2025-02-03 20:55:49,926 - INFO - Elasticsearch response: {'took': 2, 'timed_out': False, '_shards': {'total': 1, 'successful': 1, 'skipped': 0, 'failed': 0}, 'hits': {'total': {'value': 1, 'relation': 'eq'}, 'max_score': 6.6995, 'hits': [{'_index': 'tcildatav1', '_id': 'PKG012814', '_score': 6.6995, '_source': {'packageId': 'PKG012814', 'packageName': 'Simply Bali 5N Fully Loaded', 'packageTheme': ['Couple Special', 'Family', 'Adventure'], 'days': 6, 'cities': [{'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}], 'highlights': [], 'pdfName': 'PKG012814_0_20250108182726.pdf', 'price': 79769.0, 'minimumPrice': 79769.0, 'packageData': "Package ID: PKG012814 is named 'Simply Bali 5N Fully Loaded' and spans 6 days. The itinerary includes:\nDay 1 - Bali, Meals: Dinner, Description: Arrive at Bali (PVT basis) Welcome to Bali – Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who led you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 2 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast and Dinner, Description: Full Day Kintamani Hot Spring & Ubud village Tour –With Tegalalang Rice Fields (PVT Basis) Pick up for Celuk Silver Art Village Celuk Village is a traditional village which famous for the incredible gold and silver handicrafts are available around this area for very low prices. As you enter the neighborhood, you're going to feel as if you were in a jewelry exhibition. On either side of the road are established many art shops showcasing their finest works inside a glass display case. We will visit one of the best gold and silver art works in celuk village. You can take a closer look at them to appreciate it and buy some if you really like it or you can made custom jewelry based on your design. Visit Mas Wooden Carved Art Village Mas Village is one of traditional villages in Bali fundamentally as an artistic countryside by focusing the art of wood carving. This village is famous in the island as Bali Wood Carving Center located in Ubud sub district and Gianyar Regency. It owns the typical style of wood carving art by placing forward the distinguish synergy of the humanism and naturalism Visit Kintamani Hot Spring Kintamani Hot Spring features eight natural hot spring pools and one warm olympic sized pool. Heated deep within the earth, minerals from the colorless and odorless hot spring brings healing and curative powers. Enjoy a relaxing dip with the majestic panorama! *Inclusions: Natural Hot Spring Pools, Toya Water Slide with Tubes, Towel & Locker, Change & Shower Room, Facility Continue to visit Tegalalang Rice Fields The Rice terrace is designed very beautiful with exquisite hollowing rice field and precisely located on the hill bank. In this place, you will see the Balinese farmer do their rice field in oblique area complete with system irrigation. You will enjoy the beautiful panorama of valley with rice terrace and coconut trees ornament it. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Local Lunch and Dinner, Description: Full Day Ubud Bali Swing with Local Lunch & 120 Mins Spa Treatment (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. When in UBUD, Bali, one of the best points of interest not to miss is Bali Swing. Take your loved ones for a thrilling yet exciting ride on the tandem swing, or if you want to feel the sensation of flying by yourself, try the single swing that goes up to 60 meters above ground. Make your trip even more unforgettable by taking pictures in various unique photo spots available, such as adorable birds nest you can sit in ! Later enjoy the local Lunch at Bali Swing Pioneer. Proceed to spoil yourself and soothe your body and mind with our selected Balinese Massage Treatment. Using local herbs and spices along with aromatic oil, we offer a wide range of spa package including specialist treatments, facials body and foot scrub so that you can relax and escape from the stress and pressure of daily life. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast and Dinner, Description: Royal Taman Ayun & Tanah Lot Tour (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Taman Ayun Temple or Pura Taman Ayun is a magnificent family temple of Mengwi empire. This one of the most visited temple in Bali, both local & Foreign tourist. Taman Ayun Temple is also one of six royal temples in Bali making it very important both spiritually and historically. This temple’s name Taman Ayun translates to the “ Garden Temple in the Water”. Tanah Lot Temple is one of the most popular Bali Places of Interest and its an ancient Hindu Shrine perched on top of an outcrop amidst constantly crashing waves, the temple is simply among Bali not to be missed icons. The onshore site is dotted with smaller shrines alongside visitors leisure facilities that compromise restaurants, Shops and cultural park presenting regular dance performances. The temple is located in the Beraban village of the Tabanan regency, an approximate 20 km northwest of Kuta and is included on most tours to Bali western and central regions. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast and Dinner, Description: Half Day Water Sports with Uluwatu Temple Tour Followed by Kecak Dance (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Enjoy the Salty Air! Sandy Hair! Feel the tropical breeze and get closer to Indian Ocean with selected water sport activity. 1 x Jet Ski & Banana Boat Ride and Complimentary 1 x Parasailing Later proceed Uluwatu Temple sits on 70-meter-high cliff protruding above Indonesian Ocean. The main site of Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkey’s dwells here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influence. The Serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff sides. When sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’. Kecak dance is that the accompanying music is provided by the human voice, the gamelan suara, a choir of a hundred men or more sitting in concentric circle, swaying, standing up, lying prone as the story develops. Amongst the swaying masses the voices of the storytellers can be heard telling the unfolding tale. The music generated from a combination sounds of members cak which were about 50 – 70 people all of them will make music in acapella. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 6 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Depart from Kuta Morning after breakfast; you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back home to India. * The itinerary is tentative and subject to change without prior notice. Extension Nights: Travel Validity: 01 Oct – 19 Dec 2024 & 07 Jan – 31 Mar 2025 CATEGORY HOTELS PAKAGE COST: PER PERSON IN USD SINGLE TWIN / DOUBLE TRIPLE CHILD WITH BED CHILD NO BED STANDARD Hotel Siesta Legian ( Superior Room) or similar in Bali USD 40 USD 32 USD 32 USD 25 USD 10 VALUE Hotel Antanya Kuta (Deluxe Room) / Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar in Bali USD 50 USD 50 USD 50 USD 25 USD 10 PREMIUM Hotel Kuta Paradiso (Deluxe Room) or Similar in Bali USD 95 USD 90 USD 90 USD 40 USD 15 Surcharge Dates Travel Validity: 20 DEC 2024 – 05 JAN 2025 Category Hotels Pakage Cost: Per Person Per Day In USD Single Twin/Double Triple ChildWith Bed ChildNo Bed Standard Hotel Siesta Legian (Superior Room) or Similar in Dubai USD 50 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 Value Hotel Antanya Kuta (Deluxe Room) / Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar USD 50 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 Premium Kuta Paradiso (Deluxe Room) or Similar USD 50 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 Black Out Dates Surcharge - 20-Dec-2024 to 6-Jan-2025 New Year and Christmas // 26 Jan – 02 Feb 2025 Chinese New year // 28 Mar – 03 Apr 2025 Nyepi Day, GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nThe price is 79769.0. Hotels envisaged include: \nHotel\xa0Kuta Paradiso (Deluxe Room) or\xa0Similar in Bali\n, \nHotel\xa0Antanya Kuta (Deluxe Room) / Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar in Bali\n, \nHotel Siesta Legian ( Superior Room) or similar in\xa0Bali\n. Meals include: Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included. Inclusions: 05 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar in Kuta. Daily breakfast, except on Day 1 5 Dinners as per mentioned in itinerary Airport / hotel / airport transfers on (PVT Basis) Meet & Greet assistance at the airport English Speaking Driver during Transfer & Tour Half Day Water Sports with Uluwatu Temple Tour Followed by Kecak Dance (PVT Basis) Full Day Kintamani Hot Spring & Ubud village Tour –With Tegalalang Rice Fields (PVT Basis) Royal Taman Ayun & Tanah Lot Tour (PVT Basis) Full Day Ubud Bali Swing with Local Lunch & 120 Mins Spa Treatment (PVT Basis) Complimentary Welcome drink upon arrival at the Hotel & Villa Complimentary Balinese Sarong per person (adult only) as welcome gift on arrival (Adult only) Complimentary 01 bottle of Mineral Water per person on arrival Free Wi-Fi at Hotel/Villa/ Resort area Travel Insurance (Valid for the age group till 60 Yrs.). Exclusions: TCS & GST Indonesia Visa Charges Departure PCR test, if applicable All flights service Meals not mentioned in the itinerary. Any tips for guide & Driver Anything not mentioned in the inclusions. Pre & Post tour services & cost Expenditure of a personal nature (Such as uses of Mini – Bar & Refrigerator, laundry service, telephone call, camera fee, tips & Etc) All drink and beverages Hotel promotional rates not valid during Black out Period / Surcharge Dates / Stop Sales on Hotel Tourism Tax (if applicable) Midnight surcharge Blackout Dates: 15 DEC 2024 - 06 JAN 2025 The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times.. Product Terms and Conditions: Package Terms and Conditions: The upgrade hotel prices are subject to availability at the time of booking. The upgrade hotel prices DO NOT GUARANTEE rooms at the envisaged hotels. The upgrade hotel rooms are subject to availability at the time of booking. For the upgrade hotel, In case the hotel chosen is unavailable we will provide with multiple options of similar category hotel. The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times. During Peak Season: Minimum 2 Nights Stay is required No Check Out period on 31 December 2024 and 01 January 2025 Nyepi Day (Silent Day) is on 29 March 2025. No outdoor activity is allowed, and Airport will be closed from 05.59 am 29 March 2025 to 06.00 am 30 March 2025 Compulsory New Year Dinner will be Applicable according to the Resort The rates are not valid on block out dates. Surcharges as and when applicable will be advised and passengers would be requested to pay the same Surcharges could be over and above the total package price quoted to the passengers at the time of booking. Guests are requested to check with sales staff before booking their on-wards/connecting flights. The rates are subject to availability of hotel accommodation and sightseeing tours at the time of booking. We reserve the right to use an alternate hotel accommodation of an equal or higher standard. If we source a more expensive alternative, we reserve the right to re-quote based on the higher rates. Prices are not valid during Trade Fair periods. Rates are valid for Indian Passport holders only. International Check in time is 1400 hours / Check out time is 1100 hours, early check in and checkout is subject to availability and cannot be guaranteed. Transfers wherever included are without night surcharges. No refunds either in part or in full will be made for any unutilized service. All the sightseeing tours and excursions are organized by local companies. The timings and days of operation are subject to alteration. Changes if any will be intimated at the time of booking. Sightseeing’s tours are strictly based on whether conditions and also local service providers have rights to cancel the sightseeing tours without prior notice. Rates subject to change without prior notice and also for clients traveling during weekends. Offer if any can be withdrawn at any point without prior notice. Bookings once confirmed are subject to cancellation charges which shall be advised at that time. TCIL is not responsible for any change in the price due to factors not in the control of the organization. As a practice all international hotels charge a security deposit via credit card or cash, at the time of check- in for each room. The amount will vary according to the hotel and is refunded back to the clients upon check-out. Debit cards should not be offered as it will be charged immediately and refunded only after 2-3 weeks. If any additional services or mini bar or any other service is utilized at the hotel, the hotel reserves the right to charge the same on this security deposit provided by the client. TCIL would not be responsible for these transactions and these are solely between the hotels and the clients.. Highlights of the package: .", 'packageSummary': "The 'Simply Bali 5N Fully Loaded' package is a 6-day tour that takes you on an immersive journey through the island of Bali. You'll spend your time exploring the beautiful landscapes and vibrant culture of this Indonesian paradise, with visits to various locations within the island itself. The itinerary includes guided tours to explore the island's stunning beaches, temples, and rice fields, as well as opportunities to experience the local cuisine and traditional dance performances. Participants will also have a chance to visit the famous Uluwatu Temple, watch the sunset at Kuta Beach, and take part in water sports activities such as surfing or snorkeling.", 'thumbnailImage': 'BaliFullyloaded5267.jpg', 'images': ['Bali1.jpg', 'Ricefield.jpg', 'BaliSwing.jpg', 'Tanah_Lot_Temple_New_Bali_&53.jpg', 'KeckDanace.jpg', 'KeckDanace.jpg'], 'visitingCountries': ['Indonesia'], 'departureCities': ['Patna', 'Raipur', 'Kanpur', 'Chandigarh', 'Nagpur', 'Aurangabad', 'Varanasi', 'Dehra Dun', 'Kozhikode', 'Hyderabad', 'Indore', 'Goa', 'Kolkata', 'Mangalore', 'Jammu', 'Visakhapatnam', 'Madurai', 'Jaipur', 'Bhopal', 'Mumbai', 'Thiruvananthapuram', 'Pune', 'Ahmedabad', 'Guwahati', 'Lucknow', 'Delhi', 'Vadodara', 'Chennai', 'Bangalore', 'Kannur', 'Bhubaneswar', 'Coimbatore', 'Kochi', 'Surat'], 'packageItinerary': {'summary': "The 'Simply Bali 5N Fully Loaded' package is a 6-day tour that takes you on an immersive journey through the island of Bali. You'll spend your time exploring the beautiful landscapes and vibrant culture of this Indonesian paradise, with visits to various locations within the island itself. The itinerary includes guided tours to explore the island's stunning beaches, temples, and rice fields, as well as opportunities to experience the local cuisine and traditional dance performances. Participants will also have a chance to visit the famous Uluwatu Temple, watch the sunset at Kuta Beach, and take part in water sports activities such as surfing or snorkeling.", 'itinerary': ['Arrive at Bali (PVT basis) Welcome to Bali – Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who led you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner.', "Full Day Kintamani Hot Spring & Ubud village Tour –With Tegalalang Rice Fields (PVT Basis) Pick up for Celuk Silver Art Village Celuk Village is a traditional village which famous for the incredible gold and silver handicrafts are available around this area for very low prices. As you enter the neighborhood, you're going to feel as if you were in a jewelry exhibition. On either side of the road are established many art shops showcasing their finest works inside a glass display case. We will visit one of the best gold and silver art works in celuk village. You can take a closer look at them to appreciate it and buy some if you really like it or you can made custom jewelry based on your design. Visit Mas Wooden Carved Art Village Mas Village is one of traditional villages in Bali fundamentally as an artistic countryside by focusing the art of wood carving. This village is famous in the island as Bali Wood Carving Center located in Ubud sub district and Gianyar Regency. It owns the typical style of wood carving art by placing forward the distinguish synergy of the humanism and naturalism Visit Kintamani Hot Spring Kintamani Hot Spring features eight natural hot spring pools and one warm olympic sized pool. Heated deep within the earth, minerals from the colorless and odorless hot spring brings healing and curative powers. Enjoy a relaxing dip with the majestic panorama! *Inclusions: Natural Hot Spring Pools, Toya Water Slide with Tubes, Towel & Locker, Change & Shower Room, Facility Continue to visit Tegalalang Rice Fields The Rice terrace is designed very beautiful with exquisite hollowing rice field and precisely located on the hill bank. In this place, you will see the Balinese farmer do their rice field in oblique area complete with system irrigation. You will enjoy the beautiful panorama of valley with rice terrace and coconut trees ornament it. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner.", 'Full Day Ubud Bali Swing with Local Lunch & 120 Mins Spa Treatment (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. When in UBUD, Bali, one of the best points of interest not to miss is Bali Swing. Take your loved ones for a thrilling yet exciting ride on the tandem swing, or if you want to feel the sensation of flying by yourself, try the single swing that goes up to 60 meters above ground. Make your trip even more unforgettable by taking pictures in various unique photo spots available, such as adorable birds nest you can sit in ! Later enjoy the local Lunch at Bali Swing Pioneer. Proceed to spoil yourself and soothe your body and mind with our selected Balinese Massage Treatment. Using local herbs and spices along with aromatic oil, we offer a wide range of spa package including specialist treatments, facials body and foot scrub so that you can relax and escape from the stress and pressure of daily life. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali.', 'Royal Taman Ayun & Tanah Lot Tour (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Taman Ayun Temple or Pura Taman Ayun is a magnificent family temple of Mengwi empire. This one of the most visited temple in Bali, both local & Foreign tourist. Taman Ayun Temple is also one of six royal temples in Bali making it very important both spiritually and historically. This temple’s name Taman Ayun translates to the “ Garden Temple in the Water”. Tanah Lot Temple is one of the most popular Bali Places of Interest and its an ancient Hindu Shrine perched on top of an outcrop amidst constantly crashing waves, the temple is simply among Bali not to be missed icons. The onshore site is dotted with smaller shrines alongside visitors leisure facilities that compromise restaurants, Shops and cultural park presenting regular dance performances. The temple is located in the Beraban village of the Tabanan regency, an approximate 20 km northwest of Kuta and is included on most tours to Bali western and central regions. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali.', 'Half Day Water Sports with Uluwatu Temple Tour Followed by Kecak Dance (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Enjoy the Salty Air! Sandy Hair! Feel the tropical breeze and get closer to Indian Ocean with selected water sport activity. 1 x Jet Ski & Banana Boat Ride and Complimentary 1 x Parasailing Later proceed Uluwatu Temple sits on 70-meter-high cliff protruding above Indonesian Ocean. The main site of Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkey’s dwells here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influence. The Serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff sides. When sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’. Kecak dance is that the accompanying music is provided by the human voice, the gamelan suara, a choir of a hundred men or more sitting in concentric circle, swaying, standing up, lying prone as the story develops. Amongst the swaying masses the voices of the storytellers can be heard telling the unfolding tale. The music generated from a combination sounds of members cak which were about 50 – 70 people all of them will make music in acapella. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali.', 'Depart from Kuta Morning after breakfast; you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back home to India. * The itinerary is tentative and subject to change without prior notice. Extension Nights: Travel Validity: 01 Oct – 19 Dec 2024 & 07 Jan – 31 Mar 2025 CATEGORY HOTELS PAKAGE COST: PER PERSON IN USD SINGLE TWIN / DOUBLE TRIPLE CHILD WITH BED CHILD NO BED STANDARD Hotel Siesta Legian ( Superior Room) or similar in Bali USD 40 USD 32 USD 32 USD 25 USD 10 VALUE Hotel Antanya Kuta (Deluxe Room) / Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar in Bali USD 50 USD 50 USD 50 USD 25 USD 10 PREMIUM Hotel Kuta Paradiso (Deluxe Room) or Similar in Bali USD 95 USD 90 USD 90 USD 40 USD 15 Surcharge Dates Travel Validity: 20 DEC 2024 – 05 JAN 2025 Category Hotels Pakage Cost: Per Person Per Day In USD Single Twin/Double Triple ChildWith Bed ChildNo Bed Standard Hotel Siesta Legian (Superior Room) or Similar in Dubai USD 50 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 Value Hotel Antanya Kuta (Deluxe Room) / Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar USD 50 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 Premium Kuta Paradiso (Deluxe Room) or Similar USD 50 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 USD 17 Black Out Dates Surcharge - 20-Dec-2024 to 6-Jan-2025 New Year and Christmas // 26 Jan – 02 Feb 2025 Chinese New year // 28 Mar – 03 Apr 2025 Nyepi Day']}, 'hashKey': '310c06dd966411b5d2f3117533ec50f8824118636e0530117c4a8c4a3e80fc24', 'pkgSubtypeId': 4, 'pkgSubtypeName': 'FIT', 'pkgTypeId': 1}}]}}
2025-02-03 20:55:49,926 - INFO - Package found in ES: {'packageId': 'PKG012814', 'packageName': 'Simply Bali 5N Fully Loaded', 'packageTheme': ['Couple Special', 'Family', 'Adventure'], 'days': 6, 'cities': [{'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}], 'highlights': [], 'pdfName': 'PKG012814_0_20250108182726.pdf', 'price': 79769.0, 'minimumPrice': 79769.0, 'packageData': "Package ID: PKG012814 is named 'Simply Bali 5N Fully Loaded' and spans 6 days. The itinerary includes:\nDay 1 - Bali, Meals: Dinner, Description: Arrive at Bali (PVT basis) Welcome to Bali – Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who led you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 2 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast and Dinner, Description: Full Day Kintamani Hot Spring & Ubud village Tour –With Tegalalang Rice Fields (PVT Basis) Pick up for Celuk Silver Art Village Celuk Village is a traditional village which famous for the incredible gold and silver handicrafts are available around this area for very low prices. As you enter the neighborhood, you're going to feel as if you were in a jewelry exhibition. On either side of the road are established many art shops showcasing their finest works inside a glass display case. We will visit one of the best gold and silver art works in celuk village. You can take a closer look at them to appreciate it and buy some if you really like it or you can made custom jewelry based on your design. Visit Mas Wooden Carved Art Village Mas Village is one of traditional villages in Bali fundamentally as an artistic countryside by focusing the art of wood carving. This village is famous in the island as Bali Wood Carving Center located in Ubud sub district and Gianyar Regency. It owns the typical style of wood carving art by placing forward the distinguish synergy of the humanism and naturalism Visit Kintamani Hot Spring Kintamani Hot Spring features eight natural hot spring pools and one warm olympic sized pool. Heated deep within the earth, minerals from the colorless and odorless hot spring brings healing and curative powers. Enjoy a relaxing dip with the majestic panorama! *Inclusions: Natural Hot Spring Pools, Toya Water Slide with Tubes, Towel & Locker, Change & Shower Room, Facility Continue to visit Tegalalang Rice Fields The Rice terrace is designed very beautiful with exquisite hollowing rice field and precisely located on the hill bank. In this place, you will see the Balinese farmer do their rice field in oblique area complete with system irrigation. You will enjoy the beautiful panorama of valley with rice terrace and coconut trees ornament it. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Local Lunch and Dinner, Description: Full Day Ubud Bali Swing with Local Lunch & 120 Mins Spa Treatment (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. When in UBUD, Bali, one of the best points of interest not to miss is Bali Swing. Take your loved ones for a thrilling yet exciting ride on the tandem swing, or if you want to feel the sensation of flying by yourself, try the single swing that goes up to 60 meters above ground. Make your trip even more unforgettable by taking pictures in various unique photo spots available, such as adorable birds nest you can sit in ! Later enjoy the local Lunch at Bali Swing Pioneer. Proceed to spoil yourself and soothe your body and mind with our selected Balinese Massage Treatment. Using local herbs and spices along with aromatic oil, we offer a wide range of spa package including specialist treatments, facials body and foot scrub so that you can relax and escape from the stress and pressure of daily life. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast and Dinner, Description: Royal Taman Ayun & Tanah Lot Tour (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Taman Ayun Temple or Pura Taman Ayun is a magnificent family temple of Mengwi empire. This one of the most visited temple in Bali, both local & Foreign tourist. Taman Ayun Temple is also one of six royal temples in Bali making it very important both spiritually and historically. This temple’s name Taman Ayun translates to the “ Garden Temple in the Water”. Tanah Lot Temple is one of the most popular Bali Places of Interest and its an ancient Hindu Shrine perched on top of an outcrop amidst constantly crashing waves, the temple is simply among Bali not to be missed icons. The onshore site is dotted with smaller shrines alongside visitors leisure facilities that compromise restaurants, Shops and cultural park presenting regular dance performances. The temple is located in the Beraban village of the Tabanan regency, an approximate 20 km northwest of Kuta and is included on most tours to Bali western and central regions. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast and Dinner, Description: Half Day Water Sports with Uluwatu Temple Tour Followed by Kecak Dance (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Enjoy the Salty Air! Sandy Hair! Feel the tropical breeze and get closer to Indian Ocean with selected water sport activity. 1 x Jet Ski & Banana Boat Ride and Complimentary 1 x Parasailing Later proceed Uluwatu Temple sits on 70-meter-high cliff protruding above Indonesian Ocean. The main site of Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkey’s dwells here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influence. The Serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff sides. When sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’. Kecak dance is that the accompanying music is provided by the human voice, the gamelan suara, a choir of a hundred men or more sitting in concentric circle, swaying, standing up, lying prone as the story develops. Amongst the swaying masses the voices of the storytellers can be heard telling the unfolding tale. The music generated from a combination sounds of members cak which were about 50 – 70 people all of them will make music in acapella. Proceed to Indian Restaurant for Dinner. Return to hotel post the tour and spend the overnight in Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 6 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Depart from Kuta Morning after breakfast; you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back home to India. * The itinerary is tentative and subject to change without prior notice. Extension Nights: Travel Validity: 01 Oct – 19 Dec 2024 & 07 Jan – 31 Mar 2025 CATEGORY HOTELS PAKAGE COST: PER PERSON IN USD SINGLE TWIN / DOUBLE TRIPLE CHILD WITH BED CHILD NO BED STANDARD Hotel Siesta Legian ( Superior Room) or similar in Bali USD 40 USD 32 USD 32 USD 25 USD 10 VALUE Hotel Antanya Kuta (Deluxe Room) / Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar in Bali USD 50 USD 50 USD 50 USD 25 USD 10 PREMIUM Hotel Kuta Paradiso (Deluxe Room) or Similar in Bali USD 95 USD 90 USD 90 USD 40 USD 15 Surcharge Dates Travel Validity: 20 DEC 2024 – 05 JAN 2025 Category Hotels Pakage Cost: Per Person Per Day In USD Single Twin/Double Triple ChildWith Bed ChildNo Bed Standard Hotel Siesta Legian (Superior Room) or Similar in Dubai USD 50 USD 17 USD 1