2025-02-03 20:55:49,934 - INFO - Elasticsearch response: {'took': 2, 'timed_out': False, '_shards': {'total': 1, 'successful': 1, 'skipped': 0, 'failed': 0}, 'hits': {'total': {'value': 1, 'relation': 'eq'}, 'max_score': 6.6995, 'hits': [{'_index': 'tcildatav1', '_id': 'PKG012571', '_score': 6.6995, '_source': {'packageId': 'PKG012571', 'packageName': 'Albelu Bali', 'packageTheme': ['Family'], 'days': 7, 'cities': [{'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}], 'highlights': [], 'pdfName': 'PKG011302_0_20230519164442.pdf', 'price': 91839.0, 'minimumPrice': 91839.0, 'packageData': 'Package ID: PKG012571 is named \'Albelu Bali\' and spans 7 days. The itinerary includes:\nDay 1 - Bali, Meals: Lunch and Dinner (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Dinner (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures), Description: Arrival – Check in Welcome to Bali, the Land of Dreams! Upon arrival at Denpasar Airport, you will be received by our representative, who will assist you with the transfer to your hotel in Bali. Check-in, and the day is at leisure to explore the island on your own. Bali, an island of Indonesia, is so beautiful it will leave you speechless. Known for its unspoiled natural beauty, Bali has an immensely varied landscape, with rugged coastlines marked by pristine beaches, lush green hills and volcanoes, rice terraces, and dense forests, GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 2 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour Post breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit some of Bali\'s most interesting and beautiful temples and historical features including ancient carved ruins. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs. Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour - Celuk & Mas Village Today after breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs.Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. Celuk Village is a traditional village which famous for the incredible gold and silver handicrafts are available around this area for very low prices. As you enter the neighborhood, you\'re going to feel as if you were in a jewelry exhibition. On either side of the road are established many art shops showcasing their finest works inside a glass display case. We will visit one of the best gold and silver art works in celuk village. You can take a closer look at them to appreciate it and buy some if you really like it or you can made custom jewelry based on your design. Visit Mas Wooden Carved Art Village Mas Village is one of traditional villages in Bali fundamentally as an artistic countryside by focusing the art of wood carving. This village is famous in the island as Bali Wood Carving Center located in Ubud sub district and Gianyar Regency. It owns the typical style of wood carving art by placing forward the distinguish synergy of the humanism and naturalism. Free coffee tasting., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: Experience Bali Swing - Tanah Lot Sunset Tour Post breakfast, proceed for an exciting swing, the most famous Bali Swing, it offer you and experiences and amazing views. The swings are handcrafted wonders, woven from wood and rope, offer a unique and exhilarating perspective on the island\'s beauty. Soaring through verdant jungles, emerald rice terraces, Bali\'s swings are a must-do for anyone seeking an unforgettable adrenaline rush and a touch of paradise. Later arrive at Tanah Lot Floating Temple for Sunset - one of the most popular sites in Indonesia. An ancient Hindu shrine perched on top of an outcrop amidst constantly crashing waves; a not to be missed icons. The onshore site is dotted with smaller shrines alongside visitors leisure facilities that comprise restaurants, shops and a cultural park presenting regular dance performances., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa – Visit Uluwatu Temple & Kecak Dance After breakfast, proceed the beach at Tanjung Benoa near Nusa Dua Bali. Here you will enjoy the water sport activities included in your tour like - Banana boat, Parasailing and Jet Ski. (**Parasailing subjected to weather conditions) Later proceed for Ulluwatu Temple Tour; located at 70-meter-high cliff the main site on Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside the temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkeys dwell here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influences. The serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff side. When the sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & shopping Post breakfast checkout and proceed to half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Tegenungan Waterfall – Balinese Spa 1Hr - Shopping Tour Post breakfast checkout and proceed to Tegenungan Waterfall also known as Blangsinga Waterfall, is one of the most famous and biggest waterfalls in the island of Bali. With a height of 15 meters, makes Tegenungan Waterfall as the highest waterfall around the Ubud area. The Tegenungan Waterfall created from the water flows of Petanu River. Later proceed for a relaxing spa session. Enjoy the spa presenting a natural relaxation and treatment assortment for health and beauty. (60 Minutes Traditional Balinese Massage). Enjoy free time for Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 6 - Bali, Meals: Packed Breakfast, Local Lunch and Dinner (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Breakfast, Lunch and Gala Dinner (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures), Description: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Excursion to the Gates of Heaven This morning we will depart for a visit to the "The Gate of Heaven" - Pura Lempuyang Luhur temple. The name is very fitting since the temple is located on the east of the island where the sun can be seen rising in the morning beautifully right through the Gate of Heaven. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Sari Timbul Glass Factory - Tirta Empul Today after breakfast proceed to Sari Timbul Glass Factory in Bali is a fascinating destination that combines art, environment, and culture. Located in Gianyar, Bali, this glass factory has been dedicated to environmental and artistic causes in Indonesia for over 10 years. Attractions and Activities: Explore the factory\'s glass-blowing process and witness skilled artisans at work. Discover the beautiful gardens and fairy tale-like settings, perfect for Instagram-worthy photos. Visit the Sari Timbul Art Gallery, which showcases stunning glass products and local artwork. Tirta Empul Temple is built around the sacred spring at Tampak Siring. For more than a thousand years, Balinese worshipers have been drawn to Tirta Empul Temple whose sacred spring is said to have been created by Indra and to have curative properties. The tradition continues almost unchanged at the temple today. Over 1000 years old, the temple and its two bathing places have been used by the people for good health and prosperity because of the spring water\'s curative powers., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 7 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Transfer to Airport – Flight back home Proceed to the airport for your flight back home. Do spare a few minutes to share your feedback with your Tour Manager. Your valued suggestions will be most appreciated. Return home with wonderful memories of your tour with us. * The above itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice. Final Itinerary will be handed over on the day of arrival., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nThe price is 91839.0. Hotels envisaged include: Overnight stay at the Hotels, \n04 nights at Hotel Bintang Resort Kuta or similar\xa0\n02 nights at Grand Kesambi Villa or similar\n, Overnight stay at the Hotels. Meals include: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) :\n\nDaily American breakfast. (Except Day 1)\n06 Jain / Vegetarian Lunches at Indian restaurant\n06 Jain / Vegetarian Dinners at Indian restaurant\n\n(Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures):\n\nDaily American breakfast. (Except Day 1)\xa0\n05 Vegetarian Lunches at Indian restaurant\n05 Vegetarian Dinners at Indian restaurant\n01 Gala Dinner\n\nNote: Packed lunches, if applicable, will be vegetarian\n(B - Breakfast | L - Lunch | LC - Lunch coupon | PL – Packed Lunch | D – Dinner)\n\xa0, Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included. Inclusions: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) : Accommodations at the hotels specified above or similar. All local taxes including services taxes as of 01st October 2024. Insurance for the duration of the tour. Sightseeing, accommodation & services as per the above-mentioned itinerary. All transfers and excursions inclusive of entrance fees. Professional services of a friendly and multilingual THOMAS COOK Tour Manager (Subject to minimum 25 customers) or a local Representative. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) : Return economy class airfare as per the itinerary Ex Ahmedabad Accommodations at the hotels specified above or similar. Travel Insurance - Valid for 7 days up to the age of 60 years with the coverage of USD 75,000 (Excluding US & Canada) (Any further increase in the same has to be borne by the guest). Services of a professional & multilingual Thomas Cook Tour Manager/ local representative. (Subject to minimum 25 customers) Cost of the ticket taxes for the above itinerary as of 1st January 2025. Medical insurance for the duration of the tour is included in the tour price. However, any passenger above the age of 60 years and those who wish to extend their stay will be required to pay additional charges. Meals, transfers, entrances, sightseeing and surface transport as mentioned in the itinerary.. Exclusions: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) : GST and TCS as applicable Visa on arrival charges as applicable (as of 01st April 2024) the charges are approximately USD 35-40 per person If you wish to travel in advance i.e. before the published departure date as mentioned in the brochure or like to come back on a later date after the tour ends, there will be an additional charge that will be applicable (subject to availability of seats for the given dates & ticket validity) which will be advised to you by our sales staff / travel agent. Kindly note, the deviation will be actioned only 30 Days prior to departure date. Cost of Basic Travel Quota equivalent to USD 2,50,000. Applicable Government Taxes and other service charges. The tour cost does not include POE charges and passport charges. Porterage Facility. Any other expenses of personal nature such as porterage, laundry expenses, mini-bar, mineral water, telephone charges, foods and beverages that are not included as a part of the package. Additional Meals which is not specifically included in the above itinerary. Cost of excursions, city sightseeing, entrance fees and local guides availed of by the passengers, other than that mentioned in the above itinerary. Cost of Optional Excursions. Any services not mentioned in the inclusions list. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) : GST and TCS as applicable Indonesia Visa on arrival charges as applicable the charges are approximately USD 35-40 per person Any increase in the airfare charged by the airline on your air ticket presently calculated as of 01st January 2025. Guaranteed early check in or late check-out. This is completely at the discretion of the hotel and we can only put in a request for the same. Tips and porter-age Meals other than that are mentioned in your itinerary. Drinks during meals / sightseeing tours are not included Any expenses of personal nature Any services not mentioned in the inclusions list If you wish to travel in advance i.e. before the published departure date as mentioned in the brochure or like to come back on a later date after the tour ends, there will be an additional charge that will be applicable (subject to availability of seats for the given dates & ticket validity) which will be advised to you by our sales staff / travel agent. Kindly note, the deviation will be actioned only 30 Days prior to departure date. Cost of Basic Travel Quota equivalent to USD 2,50,000. Applicable Government Taxes and other service charges. The tour cost does not include POE charges and passport charges. Any other expenses of personal nature such as porterage, laundry expenses, mini-bar, mineral water, telephone charges, foods and beverages that are not included as a part of the package. Cost of excursions, city sightseeing, entrance fees and local guides availed of by the passengers, other than that mentioned in the above itinerary. Cost of Optional Excursions. Any services not mentioned in the inclusions list. Tourist Tax entering Bali (approx USD 10) to be paid by guest before arrival to Bali.. Product Terms and Conditions: Important Notes: Hotels This Package doesn’t offer city center hotels. Hotels will be located in the airport area or on the outskirts. As a 3rd person in a triple room, most hotels offer roll-away beds and room size will be the same as double room. For Child with bed: At times hotel don’t have enough roll-away beds, in that case they might give a double and a separate single room. A person 12 years and below is considered child and above 12 years, an adult. Due to international events and trade fairs you may have to stay in hotels further away from the city. Any damages caused to the hotel rooms / Coach during the stay shall be payable by the passengers. We also reserve the right to substitute a hotel of similar class if it is deemed advisable or necessary. Hotels in certain cities are not offering buffet breakfasts due to health regulations. If the same does not change by the time the tours operate, we will organize breakfasts at Indian / local restaurant. Coaches Coaches are an important part of your journeys and we request our guests to keep the coach clean. Due to hygiene factors it is not permitted to use toilets in the coach. However the tour manager will make comfort stops during long drives. Eating & drinking is not permitted in the coach. Due to limited boot space in the coach we suggest you to carry one check-in bag & one hand bag per person only Due to parking regulations and designated drop off & pick up points it is not possible to stop at all the places during the city tour. Tour Manager will try his/her best to stop coach wherever possible for a photo stop. Coaches do not have a wheelchair access. There are steps to board / alight from the coach. Coaches are forbidden inside most of the historic city centers; to preserve them from damage caused by pollution and getting overcrowded. Most of your sightseeing will be done by local buses and by foot in the historic and heritage centers. Meals All Meals are pre–set. Sightseeing Due to logistical reasons certain departures may have amendments or reverse the itinerary. However, all the services / inclusions will remain the same. Generally, you will have to walk at sightseeing places, amusement parks and at the airports sometimes for a long distance; however the same will be timely instructed by the Tour Manager. It is advisable to carry good pair of comfortable sports shoes. The tour manager and the driver will do their best to get you as close to the monuments as possible. Every Site / Monuments has its own set of rules and regulations. We need to respect this and ensure that we follow the same. All our visits are booked in advance to avoid delays, at the same time there may be delays caused due to overcrowding, local regulations, security check etc. General On some occasions you may have to join another group in case the group does not have adequate number of members. A local representative or a driver may only be there to assist you during the initial part of your tour. Security alerts and unforeseen closures may affect the itinerary. Please take extra care of your personal belongings while on the tour, every country you travel to is prone to thefts and bag snatching. TCIL will not be liable for any loss of belongings / baggage. Disabled clients shall carry their own wheelchair & be accompanied by a qualified companion who is able to provide assistance to the disabled client per their regular/routine requirements. TCIL shall not accept any liability or responsibility for any damages, loss, baggage loss, theft, injury, accident, death, breakdown or irregularity, which may occur in carrying out the tour arrangement, weather conditions, strikes, war, quarantine and any other cause whatsoever and all such loss or expense must be borne by the passengers alone. Insurance policies must be carried along all throughout while on tour. Normal insurance charges for the duration of the tour are included in the tour price. However, any passenger above the age of 60 years and those who wish to extend their stay will be required to pay additional charges. The management reserves the right to claim any additional expenses incurred due to delay or changes in schedules of train, airplane, bus, ship or other services. The Tour Manager and the company reserves the right to amend the itinerary, alter, vary or withdraw any particular departure, excursion advertised. For the convenience of our passengers, we may at times amend the itinerary to suit prevalent conditions & at the same time attain optimum utilization of the tour. All the services as per itinerary shall remain the same as it is during such amends. There are no refunds for any services i.e. meals, sightseeing etc. not utilized on tour In case you decide to change the date of your return reservation once confirmed the exact amount payable to the airline will be advised once the same is confirmed. The images used in this brochure are for representation purpose only. Tours operated are subject to RBI / GOI regulations. Part of the tour cost will be paid in USD EURO / CHF out of your BTQ at prevailing rate of exchange at the relevant time. Please refer to the Booking Form for detailed “Terms and Conditions”.. Highlights of the package: .', 'packageSummary': "The 'Albelu Bali' package is a 7-day tour that takes you on an immersive journey through the island of Bali. You'll spend your days exploring the beautiful landscapes and vibrant culture of this Indonesian paradise, with visits to various locations within the island itself. The itinerary includes guided tours to discover the island's stunning beaches, temples, and rice fields, as well as opportunities to learn about traditional Balinese dance and craft-making. You'll also have time to relax on the beach or by the pool, take a scenic drive through the countryside, and enjoy local cuisine at some of Bali's top restaurants.", 'thumbnailImage': 'Tegenungan_Waterfall_SRP.jpeg', 'images': ['840623_Bali753.jpg', 'Kintamani.jpg', 'BaliSwing.jpg', 'Kecak_Dance_Bali_753.jpg', 'TegenunganWaterfall753.jpg', 'Gatetoheaven_753.jpeg', 'Bali891.jpg'], 'visitingCountries': ['Indonesia'], 'departureCities': ['Ahmedabad', 'Joining Direct'], 'packageItinerary': {'summary': "The 'Albelu Bali' package is a 7-day tour that takes you on an immersive journey through the island of Bali. You'll spend your days exploring the beautiful landscapes and vibrant culture of this Indonesian paradise, with visits to various locations within the island itself. The itinerary includes guided tours to discover the island's stunning beaches, temples, and rice fields, as well as opportunities to learn about traditional Balinese dance and craft-making. You'll also have time to relax on the beach or by the pool, take a scenic drive through the countryside, and enjoy local cuisine at some of Bali's top restaurants.", 'itinerary': ['Arrival – Check in Welcome to Bali, the Land of Dreams! Upon arrival at Denpasar Airport, you will be received by our representative, who will assist you with the transfer to your hotel in Bali. Check-in, and the day is at leisure to explore the island on your own. Bali, an island of Indonesia, is so beautiful it will leave you speechless. Known for its unspoiled natural beauty, Bali has an immensely varied landscape, with rugged coastlines marked by pristine beaches, lush green hills and volcanoes, rice terraces, and dense forests', "(Valid till March 2025 Departure) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour Post breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit some of Bali's most interesting and beautiful temples and historical features including ancient carved ruins. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs. Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour - Celuk & Mas Village Today after breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs.Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. Celuk Village is a traditional village which famous for the incredible gold and silver handicrafts are available around this area for very low prices. As you enter the neighborhood, you're going to feel as if you were in a jewelry exhibition. On either side of the road are established many art shops showcasing their finest works inside a glass display case. We will visit one of the best gold and silver art works in celuk village. You can take a closer look at them to appreciate it and buy some if you really like it or you can made custom jewelry based on your design. Visit Mas Wooden Carved Art Village Mas Village is one of traditional villages in Bali fundamentally as an artistic countryside by focusing the art of wood carving. This village is famous in the island as Bali Wood Carving Center located in Ubud sub district and Gianyar Regency. It owns the typical style of wood carving art by placing forward the distinguish synergy of the humanism and naturalism. Free coffee tasting.", "Experience Bali Swing - Tanah Lot Sunset Tour Post breakfast, proceed for an exciting swing, the most famous Bali Swing, it offer you and experiences and amazing views. The swings are handcrafted wonders, woven from wood and rope, offer a unique and exhilarating perspective on the island's beauty. Soaring through verdant jungles, emerald rice terraces, Bali's swings are a must-do for anyone seeking an unforgettable adrenaline rush and a touch of paradise. Later arrive at Tanah Lot Floating Temple for Sunset - one of the most popular sites in Indonesia. An ancient Hindu shrine perched on top of an outcrop amidst constantly crashing waves; a not to be missed icons. The onshore site is dotted with smaller shrines alongside visitors leisure facilities that comprise restaurants, shops and a cultural park presenting regular dance performances.", 'Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa – Visit Uluwatu Temple & Kecak Dance After breakfast, proceed the beach at Tanjung Benoa near Nusa Dua Bali. Here you will enjoy the water sport activities included in your tour like - Banana boat, Parasailing and Jet Ski. (**Parasailing subjected to weather conditions) Later proceed for Ulluwatu Temple Tour; located at 70-meter-high cliff the main site on Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside the temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkeys dwell here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influences. The serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff side. When the sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’.', '(Valid till March 2025 Departure) Half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & shopping Post breakfast checkout and proceed to half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Tegenungan Waterfall – Balinese Spa 1Hr - Shopping Tour Post breakfast checkout and proceed to Tegenungan Waterfall also known as Blangsinga Waterfall, is one of the most famous and biggest waterfalls in the island of Bali. With a height of 15 meters, makes Tegenungan Waterfall as the highest waterfall around the Ubud area. The Tegenungan Waterfall created from the water flows of Petanu River. Later proceed for a relaxing spa session. Enjoy the spa presenting a natural relaxation and treatment assortment for health and beauty. (60 Minutes Traditional Balinese Massage). Enjoy free time for Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay.', '(Valid till March 2025 Departure) Excursion to the Gates of Heaven This morning we will depart for a visit to the "The Gate of Heaven" - Pura Lempuyang Luhur temple. The name is very fitting since the temple is located on the east of the island where the sun can be seen rising in the morning beautifully right through the Gate of Heaven. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Sari Timbul Glass Factory - Tirta Empul Today after breakfast proceed to Sari Timbul Glass Factory in Bali is a fascinating destination that combines art, environment, and culture. Located in Gianyar, Bali, this glass factory has been dedicated to environmental and artistic causes in Indonesia for over 10 years. Attractions and Activities: Explore the factory\'s glass-blowing process and witness skilled artisans at work. Discover the beautiful gardens and fairy tale-like settings, perfect for Instagram-worthy photos. Visit the Sari Timbul Art Gallery, which showcases stunning glass products and local artwork. Tirta Empul Temple is built around the sacred spring at Tampak Siring. For more than a thousand years, Balinese worshipers have been drawn to Tirta Empul Temple whose sacred spring is said to have been created by Indra and to have curative properties. The tradition continues almost unchanged at the temple today. Over 1000 years old, the temple and its two bathing places have been used by the people for good health and prosperity because of the spring water\'s curative powers.', 'Transfer to Airport – Flight back home Proceed to the airport for your flight back home. Do spare a few minutes to share your feedback with your Tour Manager. Your valued suggestions will be most appreciated. Return home with wonderful memories of your tour with us. * The above itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice. Final Itinerary will be handed over on the day of arrival.']}, 'hashKey': '6da6da165ecdbd6aa5560f2c33c213cef3332cdc1cc3e536460a5b1fd159f1ea', 'pkgSubtypeId': 3, 'pkgSubtypeName': 'GIT', 'pkgTypeId': 1}}]}}
2025-02-03 20:55:49,935 - INFO - Package found in ES: {'packageId': 'PKG012571', 'packageName': 'Albelu Bali', 'packageTheme': ['Family'], 'days': 7, 'cities': [{'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}], 'highlights': [], 'pdfName': 'PKG011302_0_20230519164442.pdf', 'price': 91839.0, 'minimumPrice': 91839.0, 'packageData': 'Package ID: PKG012571 is named \'Albelu Bali\' and spans 7 days. The itinerary includes:\nDay 1 - Bali, Meals: Lunch and Dinner (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Dinner (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures), Description: Arrival – Check in Welcome to Bali, the Land of Dreams! Upon arrival at Denpasar Airport, you will be received by our representative, who will assist you with the transfer to your hotel in Bali. Check-in, and the day is at leisure to explore the island on your own. Bali, an island of Indonesia, is so beautiful it will leave you speechless. Known for its unspoiled natural beauty, Bali has an immensely varied landscape, with rugged coastlines marked by pristine beaches, lush green hills and volcanoes, rice terraces, and dense forests, GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 2 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour Post breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit some of Bali\'s most interesting and beautiful temples and historical features including ancient carved ruins. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs. Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour - Celuk & Mas Village Today after breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs.Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. Celuk Village is a traditional village which famous for the incredible gold and silver handicrafts are available around this area for very low prices. As you enter the neighborhood, you\'re going to feel as if you were in a jewelry exhibition. On either side of the road are established many art shops showcasing their finest works inside a glass display case. We will visit one of the best gold and silver art works in celuk village. You can take a closer look at them to appreciate it and buy some if you really like it or you can made custom jewelry based on your design. Visit Mas Wooden Carved Art Village Mas Village is one of traditional villages in Bali fundamentally as an artistic countryside by focusing the art of wood carving. This village is famous in the island as Bali Wood Carving Center located in Ubud sub district and Gianyar Regency. It owns the typical style of wood carving art by placing forward the distinguish synergy of the humanism and naturalism. Free coffee tasting., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: Experience Bali Swing - Tanah Lot Sunset Tour Post breakfast, proceed for an exciting swing, the most famous Bali Swing, it offer you and experiences and amazing views. The swings are handcrafted wonders, woven from wood and rope, offer a unique and exhilarating perspective on the island\'s beauty. Soaring through verdant jungles, emerald rice terraces, Bali\'s swings are a must-do for anyone seeking an unforgettable adrenaline rush and a touch of paradise. Later arrive at Tanah Lot Floating Temple for Sunset - one of the most popular sites in Indonesia. An ancient Hindu shrine perched on top of an outcrop amidst constantly crashing waves; a not to be missed icons. The onshore site is dotted with smaller shrines alongside visitors leisure facilities that comprise restaurants, shops and a cultural park presenting regular dance performances., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa – Visit Uluwatu Temple & Kecak Dance After breakfast, proceed the beach at Tanjung Benoa near Nusa Dua Bali. Here you will enjoy the water sport activities included in your tour like - Banana boat, Parasailing and Jet Ski. (**Parasailing subjected to weather conditions) Later proceed for Ulluwatu Temple Tour; located at 70-meter-high cliff the main site on Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside the temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkeys dwell here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influences. The serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff side. When the sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner, Description: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & shopping Post breakfast checkout and proceed to half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Tegenungan Waterfall – Balinese Spa 1Hr - Shopping Tour Post breakfast checkout and proceed to Tegenungan Waterfall also known as Blangsinga Waterfall, is one of the most famous and biggest waterfalls in the island of Bali. With a height of 15 meters, makes Tegenungan Waterfall as the highest waterfall around the Ubud area. The Tegenungan Waterfall created from the water flows of Petanu River. Later proceed for a relaxing spa session. Enjoy the spa presenting a natural relaxation and treatment assortment for health and beauty. (60 Minutes Traditional Balinese Massage). Enjoy free time for Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 6 - Bali, Meals: Packed Breakfast, Local Lunch and Dinner (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Breakfast, Lunch and Gala Dinner (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures), Description: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) Excursion to the Gates of Heaven This morning we will depart for a visit to the "The Gate of Heaven" - Pura Lempuyang Luhur temple. The name is very fitting since the temple is located on the east of the island where the sun can be seen rising in the morning beautifully right through the Gate of Heaven. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Sari Timbul Glass Factory - Tirta Empul Today after breakfast proceed to Sari Timbul Glass Factory in Bali is a fascinating destination that combines art, environment, and culture. Located in Gianyar, Bali, this glass factory has been dedicated to environmental and artistic causes in Indonesia for over 10 years. Attractions and Activities: Explore the factory\'s glass-blowing process and witness skilled artisans at work. Discover the beautiful gardens and fairy tale-like settings, perfect for Instagram-worthy photos. Visit the Sari Timbul Art Gallery, which showcases stunning glass products and local artwork. Tirta Empul Temple is built around the sacred spring at Tampak Siring. For more than a thousand years, Balinese worshipers have been drawn to Tirta Empul Temple whose sacred spring is said to have been created by Indra and to have curative properties. The tradition continues almost unchanged at the temple today. Over 1000 years old, the temple and its two bathing places have been used by the people for good health and prosperity because of the spring water\'s curative powers., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 7 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Transfer to Airport – Flight back home Proceed to the airport for your flight back home. Do spare a few minutes to share your feedback with your Tour Manager. Your valued suggestions will be most appreciated. Return home with wonderful memories of your tour with us. * The above itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice. Final Itinerary will be handed over on the day of arrival., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nThe price is 91839.0. Hotels envisaged include: Overnight stay at the Hotels, \n04 nights at Hotel Bintang Resort Kuta or similar\xa0\n02 nights at Grand Kesambi Villa or similar\n, Overnight stay at the Hotels. Meals include: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) :\n\nDaily American breakfast. (Except Day 1)\n06 Jain / Vegetarian Lunches at Indian restaurant\n06 Jain / Vegetarian Dinners at Indian restaurant\n\n(Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures):\n\nDaily American breakfast. (Except Day 1)\xa0\n05 Vegetarian Lunches at Indian restaurant\n05 Vegetarian Dinners at Indian restaurant\n01 Gala Dinner\n\nNote: Packed lunches, if applicable, will be vegetarian\n(B - Breakfast | L - Lunch | LC - Lunch coupon | PL – Packed Lunch | D – Dinner)\n\xa0, Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included. Inclusions: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) : Accommodations at the hotels specified above or similar. All local taxes including services taxes as of 01st October 2024. Insurance for the duration of the tour. Sightseeing, accommodation & services as per the above-mentioned itinerary. All transfers and excursions inclusive of entrance fees. Professional services of a friendly and multilingual THOMAS COOK Tour Manager (Subject to minimum 25 customers) or a local Representative. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) : Return economy class airfare as per the itinerary Ex Ahmedabad Accommodations at the hotels specified above or similar. Travel Insurance - Valid for 7 days up to the age of 60 years with the coverage of USD 75,000 (Excluding US & Canada) (Any further increase in the same has to be borne by the guest). Services of a professional & multilingual Thomas Cook Tour Manager/ local representative. (Subject to minimum 25 customers) Cost of the ticket taxes for the above itinerary as of 1st January 2025. Medical insurance for the duration of the tour is included in the tour price. However, any passenger above the age of 60 years and those who wish to extend their stay will be required to pay additional charges. Meals, transfers, entrances, sightseeing and surface transport as mentioned in the itinerary.. Exclusions: (Valid till March 2025 Departure) : GST and TCS as applicable Visa on arrival charges as applicable (as of 01st April 2024) the charges are approximately USD 35-40 per person If you wish to travel in advance i.e. before the published departure date as mentioned in the brochure or like to come back on a later date after the tour ends, there will be an additional charge that will be applicable (subject to availability of seats for the given dates & ticket validity) which will be advised to you by our sales staff / travel agent. Kindly note, the deviation will be actioned only 30 Days prior to departure date. Cost of Basic Travel Quota equivalent to USD 2,50,000. Applicable Government Taxes and other service charges. The tour cost does not include POE charges and passport charges. Porterage Facility. Any other expenses of personal nature such as porterage, laundry expenses, mini-bar, mineral water, telephone charges, foods and beverages that are not included as a part of the package. Additional Meals which is not specifically included in the above itinerary. Cost of excursions, city sightseeing, entrance fees and local guides availed of by the passengers, other than that mentioned in the above itinerary. Cost of Optional Excursions. Any services not mentioned in the inclusions list. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) : GST and TCS as applicable Indonesia Visa on arrival charges as applicable the charges are approximately USD 35-40 per person Any increase in the airfare charged by the airline on your air ticket presently calculated as of 01st January 2025. Guaranteed early check in or late check-out. This is completely at the discretion of the hotel and we can only put in a request for the same. Tips and porter-age Meals other than that are mentioned in your itinerary. Drinks during meals / sightseeing tours are not included Any expenses of personal nature Any services not mentioned in the inclusions list If you wish to travel in advance i.e. before the published departure date as mentioned in the brochure or like to come back on a later date after the tour ends, there will be an additional charge that will be applicable (subject to availability of seats for the given dates & ticket validity) which will be advised to you by our sales staff / travel agent. Kindly note, the deviation will be actioned only 30 Days prior to departure date. Cost of Basic Travel Quota equivalent to USD 2,50,000. Applicable Government Taxes and other service charges. The tour cost does not include POE charges and passport charges. Any other expenses of personal nature such as porterage, laundry expenses, mini-bar, mineral water, telephone charges, foods and beverages that are not included as a part of the package. Cost of excursions, city sightseeing, entrance fees and local guides availed of by the passengers, other than that mentioned in the above itinerary. Cost of Optional Excursions. Any services not mentioned in the inclusions list. Tourist Tax entering Bali (approx USD 10) to be paid by guest before arrival to Bali.. Product Terms and Conditions: Important Notes: Hotels This Package doesn’t offer city center hotels. Hotels will be located in the airport area or on the outskirts. As a 3rd person in a triple room, most hotels offer roll-away beds and room size will be the same as double room. For Child with bed: At times hotel don’t have enough roll-away beds, in that case they might give a double and a separate single room. A person 12 years and below is considered child and above 12 years, an adult. Due to international events and trade fairs you may have to stay in hotels further away from the city. Any damages caused to the hotel rooms / Coach during the stay shall be payable by the passengers. We also reserve the right to substitute a hotel of similar class if it is deemed advisable or necessary. Hotels in certain cities are not offering buffet breakfasts due to health regulations. If the same does not change by the time the tours operate, we will organize breakfasts at Indian / local restaurant. Coaches Coaches are an important part of your journeys and we request our guests to keep the coach clean. Due to hygiene factors it is not permitted to use toilets in the coach. However the tour manager will make comfort stops during long drives. Eating & drinking is not permitted in the coach. Due to limited boot space in the coach we suggest you to carry one check-in bag & one hand bag per person only Due to parking regulations and designated drop off & pick up points it is not possible to stop at all the places during the city tour. Tour Manager will try his/her best to stop coach wherever possible for a photo stop. Coaches do not have a wheelchair access. There are steps to board / alight from the coach. Coaches are forbidden inside most of the historic city centers; to preserve them from damage caused by pollution and getting overcrowded. Most of your sightseeing will be done by local buses and by foot in the historic and heritage centers. Meals All Meals are pre–set. Sightseeing Due to logistical reasons certain departures may have amendments or reverse the itinerary. However, all the services / inclusions will remain the same. Generally, you will have to walk at sightseeing places, amusement parks and at the airports sometimes for a long distance; however the same will be timely instructed by the Tour Manager. It is advisable to carry good pair of comfortable sports shoes. The tour manager and the driver will do their best to get you as close to the monuments as possible. Every Site / Monuments has its own set of rules and regulations. We need to respect this and ensure that we follow the same. All our visits are booked in advance to avoid delays, at the same time there may be delays caused due to overcrowding, local regulations, security check etc. General On some occasions you may have to join another group in case the group does not have adequate number of members. A local representative or a driver may only be there to assist you during the initial part of your tour. Security alerts and unforeseen closures may affect the itinerary. Please take extra care of your personal belongings while on the tour, every country you travel to is prone to thefts and bag snatching. TCIL will not be liable for any loss of belongings / baggage. Disabled clients shall carry their own wheelchair & be accompanied by a qualified companion who is able to provide assistance to the disabled client per their regular/routine requirements. TCIL shall not accept any liability or responsibility for any damages, loss, baggage loss, theft, injury, accident, death, breakdown or irregularity, which may occur in carrying out the tour arrangement, weather conditions, strikes, war, quarantine and any other cause whatsoever and all such loss or expense must be borne by the passengers alone. Insurance policies must be carried along all throughout while on tour. Normal insurance charges for the duration of the tour are included in the tour price. However, any passenger above the age of 60 years and those who wish to extend their stay will be required to pay additional charges. The management reserves the right to claim any additional expenses incurred due to delay or changes in schedules of train, airplane, bus, ship or other services. The Tour Manager and the company reserves the right to amend the itinerary, alter, vary or withdraw any particular departure, excursion advertised. For the convenience of our passengers, we may at times amend the itinerary to suit prevalent conditions & at the same time attain optimum utilization of the tour. All the services as per itinerary shall remain the same as it is during such amends. There are no refunds for any services i.e. meals, sightseeing etc. not utilized on tour In case you decide to change the date of your return reservation once confirmed the exact amount payable to the airline will be advised once the same is confirmed. The images used in this brochure are for representation purpose only. Tours operated are subject to RBI / GOI regulations. Part of the tour cost will be paid in USD EURO / CHF out of your BTQ at prevailing rate of exchange at the relevant time. Please refer to the Booking Form for detailed “Terms and Conditions”.. Highlights of the package: .', 'packageSummary': "The 'Albelu Bali' package is a 7-day tour that takes you on an immersive journey through the island of Bali. You'll spend your days exploring the beautiful landscapes and vibrant culture of this Indonesian paradise, with visits to various locations within the island itself. The itinerary includes guided tours to discover the island's stunning beaches, temples, and rice fields, as well as opportunities to learn about traditional Balinese dance and craft-making. You'll also have time to relax on the beach or by the pool, take a scenic drive through the countryside, and enjoy local cuisine at some of Bali's top restaurants.", 'thumbnailImage': 'Tegenungan_Waterfall_SRP.jpeg', 'images': ['840623_Bali753.jpg', 'Kintamani.jpg', 'BaliSwing.jpg', 'Kecak_Dance_Bali_753.jpg', 'TegenunganWaterfall753.jpg', 'Gatetoheaven_753.jpeg', 'Bali891.jpg'], 'visitingCountries': ['Indonesia'], 'departureCities': ['Ahmedabad', 'Joining Direct'], 'packageItinerary': {'summary': "The 'Albelu Bali' package is a 7-day tour that takes you on an immersive journey through the island of Bali. You'll spend your days exploring the beautiful landscapes and vibrant culture of this Indonesian paradise, with visits to various locations within the island itself. The itinerary includes guided tours to discover the island's stunning beaches, temples, and rice fields, as well as opportunities to learn about traditional Balinese dance and craft-making. You'll also have time to relax on the beach or by the pool, take a scenic drive through the countryside, and enjoy local cuisine at some of Bali's top restaurants.", 'itinerary': ['Arrival – Check in Welcome to Bali, the Land of Dreams! Upon arrival at Denpasar Airport, you will be received by our representative, who will assist you with the transfer to your hotel in Bali. Check-in, and the day is at leisure to explore the island on your own. Bali, an island of Indonesia, is so beautiful it will leave you speechless. Known for its unspoiled natural beauty, Bali has an immensely varied landscape, with rugged coastlines marked by pristine beaches, lush green hills and volcanoes, rice terraces, and dense forests', "(Valid till March 2025 Departure) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour Post breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit some of Bali's most interesting and beautiful temples and historical features including ancient carved ruins. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs. Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Day excursion - Kintamani and Ubud Village Tour - Celuk & Mas Village Today after breakfast, proceed on a guided tour of Kintamani – explore some of the most desirable and beautiful areas located in the northeast of Bali including incredible views of the Mount Batur volcano and the lakes. We will visit the traditional markets which offer an opportunity to buy souvenirs.Later proceed for the Ubud Village Tour - one of the most famous villages of Bali, located amongst rice paddies and steep ravines in the central foot hills of the Gianyar regency. Celuk Village is a traditional village which famous for the incredible gold and silver handicrafts are available around this area for very low prices. As you enter the neighborhood, you're going to feel as if you were in a jewelry exhibition. On either side of the road are established many art shops showcasing their finest works inside a glass display case. We will visit one of the best gold and silver art works in celuk village. You can take a closer look at them to appreciate it and buy some if you really like it or you can made custom jewelry based on your design. Visit Mas Wooden Carved Art Village Mas Village is one of traditional villages in Bali fundamentally as an artistic countryside by focusing the art of wood carving. This village is famous in the island as Bali Wood Carving Center located in Ubud sub district and Gianyar Regency. It owns the typical style of wood carving art by placing forward the distinguish synergy of the humanism and naturalism. Free coffee tasting.", "Experience Bali Swing - Tanah Lot Sunset Tour Post breakfast, proceed for an exciting swing, the most famous Bali Swing, it offer you and experiences and amazing views. The swings are handcrafted wonders, woven from wood and rope, offer a unique and exhilarating perspective on the island's beauty. Soaring through verdant jungles, emerald rice terraces, Bali's swings are a must-do for anyone seeking an unforgettable adrenaline rush and a touch of paradise. Later arrive at Tanah Lot Floating Temple for Sunset - one of the most popular sites in Indonesia. An ancient Hindu shrine perched on top of an outcrop amidst constantly crashing waves; a not to be missed icons. The onshore site is dotted with smaller shrines alongside visitors leisure facilities that comprise restaurants, shops and a cultural park presenting regular dance performances.", 'Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa – Visit Uluwatu Temple & Kecak Dance After breakfast, proceed the beach at Tanjung Benoa near Nusa Dua Bali. Here you will enjoy the water sport activities included in your tour like - Banana boat, Parasailing and Jet Ski. (**Parasailing subjected to weather conditions) Later proceed for Ulluwatu Temple Tour; located at 70-meter-high cliff the main site on Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside the temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkeys dwell here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influences. The serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff side. When the sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’.', '(Valid till March 2025 Departure) Half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & shopping Post breakfast checkout and proceed to half day tour to Tegenungan waterfall & Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Tegenungan Waterfall – Balinese Spa 1Hr - Shopping Tour Post breakfast checkout and proceed to Tegenungan Waterfall also known as Blangsinga Waterfall, is one of the most famous and biggest waterfalls in the island of Bali. With a height of 15 meters, makes Tegenungan Waterfall as the highest waterfall around the Ubud area. The Tegenungan Waterfall created from the water flows of Petanu River. Later proceed for a relaxing spa session. Enjoy the spa presenting a natural relaxation and treatment assortment for health and beauty. (60 Minutes Traditional Balinese Massage). Enjoy free time for Shopping. Later check in to your Villa for an exclusive stay.', '(Valid till March 2025 Departure) Excursion to the Gates of Heaven This morning we will depart for a visit to the "The Gate of Heaven" - Pura Lempuyang Luhur temple. The name is very fitting since the temple is located on the east of the island where the sun can be seen rising in the morning beautifully right through the Gate of Heaven. (Valid from April 2025 to December 2025 Departures) Sari Timbul Glass Factory - Tirta Empul Today after breakfast proceed to Sari Timbul Glass Factory in Bali is a fascinating destination that combines art, environment, and culture. Located in Gianyar, Bali, this glass factory has been dedicated to environmental and artistic causes in Indonesia for over 10 years. Attractions and Activities: Explore the factory\'s glass-blowing process and witness skilled artisans at work. Discover the beautiful gardens and fairy tale-like settings, perfect for Instagram-worthy photos. Visit the Sari Timbul Art Gallery, which showcases stunning glass products and local artwork. Tirta Empul Temple is built around the sacred spring at Tampak Siring. For more than a thousand years, Balinese worshipers have been drawn to Tirta Empul Temple whose sacred spring is said to have been created by Indra and to have curative properties. The tradition continues almost unchanged at the temple today. Over 1000 years old, the temple and its two bathing places have been used by the people for good health and prosperity because of the spring water\'s curative powers.', 'Transfer to Airport – Flight back home Proceed to the airport for your flight back home. Do spare a few minutes to share your feedback with your Tour Manager. Your valued suggestions will be most appreciated. Return home with wonderful memories of your tour with us. * The above itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice. Final Itinerary will be handed over on the day of arrival.']}, 'hashKey': '6da6da165ecdbd6aa5560f2c33c213cef3332cdc1cc3e536460a5b1fd159f1ea', 'pkgSubtypeId': 3, 'pkgSubtypeName': 'GIT', 'pkgTypeId': 1}
