ces Entrance fees Blackout Dates: 15th Dec 2023 – 05 Jan 2024 Meals not mentioned in the itinerary. Any tips - for guide & Driver Anything not mentioned in the inclusions. Pre & Post tour services & cost Expenditure of a personal nature (Such as uses of Mini – Bar & Refrigerator, laundry service, telephone call, camera fee, tips & Etc.) All drink and beverages Hotel promotional rates not valid during Black out Period / Surcharge Dates / Stop Sales on Hotel Tourism Tax (if applicable) Midnight surcharge The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times.. Product Terms and Conditions: Black Out/Surcharges Dates: 15 Dec 2024 – 05 Jan 2025 The above prices will not be valid for any block out date/ period which is informed during confirmation of the booking; if any change in the price, the same will be applicable for all bookings and to be borne by the customer Terms and Conditions: The upgrade hotel prices are subject to availability at the time of booking. The upgrade hotel prices DO NOT GUARANTEE rooms at the envisaged hotels. The upgrade hotel rooms are subject to availability at the time of booking. For the upgrade hotel, In case the hotel chosen is unavailable we will provide with multiple options of similar category hotel. The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times. The rates are not valid on block out dates. Surcharges as and when applicable will be advised and passengers would be requested to pay the same. Surcharges could be over and above the total package price quoted to the passengers at the time of booking. Guests are requested to check with sales staff before booking their on-wards/connecting flights. The rates are subject to availability of hotel accommodation and sightseeing tours at the time of booking. We reserve the right to use an alternate hotel accommodation of an equal or higher standard. If we source a more expensive alternative, we reserve the right to re-quote based on the higher rates. Prices are not valid during Trade Fair periods. Rates are valid for Indian Passport holders only. International Check in time is 1400 hours / Check out time is 1100 hours, early check in and checkout is subject to availability and cannot be guaranteed. Transfers wherever included are without night surcharges. No refunds either in part or in full will be made for any unutilized service. All the sightseeing tours and excursions are organized by local companies. The timings and days of operation are subject to alteration. Changes if any will be intimated at the time of booking. Sightseeing’s tours are strictly based on whether conditions and also local service providers have rights to cancel the sightseeing tours without prior notice. Rates subject to change without prior notice and also for clients traveling during weekends. Offer if any can be withdrawn at any point without prior notice. Bookings once confirmed are subject to cancellation charges which shall be advised at that time. TCIL is not responsible for any change in the price due to factors not in the control of the organization. As a practice all international hotels charge a security deposit via credit card or cash, at the time of check- in for each room. The amount will vary according to the hotel and is refunded back to the clients upon check-out. Debit cards should not be offered as it will be charged immediately and refunded only after 2-3 weeks. If any additional services or mini bar or any other service is utilized at the hotel, the hotel reserves the right to charge the same on this security deposit provided by the client. TCIL would not be responsible for these transactions and these are solely between the hotels and the clients.. Highlights of the package: .", 'packageSummary': "The 'Blissful Bali - Honeymoon Special' package is an 8-day romantic getaway covering the beautiful island of Bali. This enchanting journey takes you through the vibrant streets of Kuta, the cultural hub of Ubud, and the luxurious resorts of Seminyak, with multiple visits to each destination allowing for a deeper exploration of the island's charms. The itinerary includes a scenic drive through the lush rice fields, a visit to the famous Uluwatu Temple perched on a cliff overlooking the Indian Ocean, a romantic sunset dinner at a beachside restaurant, and a rejuvenating couples' spa treatment at a luxurious resort. You'll also have the opportunity to take a cooking class, learn traditional Balinese dance, and enjoy a leisurely boat ride through the island's picturesque waters.", 'thumbnailImage': 'Bali_Couple_SRP.jpg', 'images': ['Kuta.jpeg', 'Bananaboat.jpg', 'Baliswing_new_753.jpeg', 'Bali75309.jpg', 'Gatetheaven7531.jpg', 'Seminyak753.jpg', 'NusaPenida753.jpg', 'Bali_Scenic_7531.jpg'], 'visitingCountries': ['Indonesia'], 'departureCities': ['Hyderabad', 'Ahmedabad', 'Srinagar', 'Pune', 'Surat', 'Kochi', 'Amritsar', 'Bangalore', 'Nagpur', 'Goa', 'Jammu', 'Chandigarh', 'Thiruvananthapuram', 'Allahabad', 'Aurangabad', 'Guwahati', 'Patna', 'Indore', 'Kolkata', 'Varanasi', 'Udaipur', 'Lucknow', 'Bhubaneswar', 'Mumbai', 'Bhopal', 'Delhi', 'Chennai', 'Bagdogra', 'Jaipur', 'Mangalore', 'Kozhikode', 'Imphal'], 'packageItinerary': {'summary': "The 'Blissful Bali - Honeymoon Special' package is an 8-day romantic getaway covering the beautiful island of Bali. This enchanting journey takes you through the vibrant streets of Kuta, the cultural hub of Ubud, and the luxurious resorts of Seminyak, with multiple visits to each destination allowing for a deeper exploration of the island's charms. The itinerary includes a scenic drive through the lush rice fields, a visit to the famous Uluwatu Temple perched on a cliff overlooking the Indian Ocean, a romantic sunset dinner at a beachside restaurant, and a rejuvenating couples' spa treatment at a luxurious resort. You'll also have the opportunity to take a cooking class, learn traditional Balinese dance, and enjoy a leisurely boat ride through the island's picturesque waters.", 'itinerary': ['Kuta Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who led you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. It takes about 20 minutes’ drive from airport to your hotel or more depending on the traffic. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up.', 'Half Day ATV Quad Bike on Private Basis & Half Day Benoa Beach Tour including Banana Boat on private basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel For a hard core adventurer or a novice, off-roading is the most appealing word & what better than Quad Biking while in Bali. Ride off the beaten track during your Bali vacation on your own All-Terrain Vehicle (ATV). Follow an experienced guide along a challenging track, suitable for all skill levels. One can also enjoy as a co-pilot if you do not want to do it independently. No driving license required & safety is of utmost priority here. Glide past a picturesque landscape of rice fields, bamboo forest, and lush riverside flanked by traditional Balinese villages. It is an ultimate thrill for a couple of hours, you will just want to keep it going. An ideal Bali holiday is incomplete without water sports & what better than the famous Tanjung Benoa beach. This beach best known for its aquatic adventure is located in the Benoa peninsula far away from the hustle & bustle. North of Nusa Dua this beach offers a wide range of water sports from Parasailing to Banana boat ride & so on. Please check with our representatives for all the water sports information. Many shacks & restaurants lined up along the beach make sure that your tummy is full & you enjoy the most.', 'Half Day Authentic Balinese Massage (60 min) on Private Basis + Bali Swing on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A Bali holiday isn’t complete without an authentic spa experience. Balinese spa treatments are well-known the world over for their healing properties as well as the hospitality by the locals. Refresh your mind, body & soul with a perfect blend of traditional therapeutic remedies & modern day spa rituals. Enjoy this delightful massage & rejuvenate yourself to the core. Swings in Bali are the most trending activities across all social media platforms. And the experiences definitely justify the popularity. Set in Ubud you must try and enjoy this incredible experience. A professional swing guide, will company you to catch the unforgettable memory. Proper set of instructions will guide you through the equipment & safety standards. Soak in the pleasure of being a free bird, reminiscing through your childhood days.', 'Transfer from Kuta to Ubud, Sunset Dinner Cruise on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Inter Hotel Transfer Kuta Hotel to Ubud Hotel on Private Basis No better way than a Sunset Dinner Cruise on a balmy tropical evening. As the daylight fades & the Sun goes into oblivion, you set off on a relaxing short voyage around the alluring Bali harbor & its surrounding areas. Seize the moments, in the cool & calm environs of the top deck aboard the vessel. A plethora of activities will make your evening more memorable. Soak in to the live musical experiences at the bridge deck, savour wide array of delectable international buffet dinner & also witnesses the live Cabaret show. Dance the night away like no one’s watching. Definitely a treat for all age groups but highly recommended for the honeymooners. A remarkable evening well spent on board the Sunset dinner cruise will always give you nostalgia for life.', 'Full Day Lempuyang Temple Tour on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Ever wondered what its like actually to visit The Gates of Heaven. If you are visiting Bali, then this popular place must be on your list of things to see and do. Most people visit here to get an epic shot between the Candi Bentar â€“ The Gateway. This Candi Bentar is a split gateway seen in almost all Balinese entrances of religious compounds. Usually, these gateways have staircases that lead to its centre point. The two sides represent the Balinese concept of duality and the importance of maintaining a balance between darkness & the bright forces. While you will see Candi Bentars everywhere in Bali, the Gates of Heaven at Lempuyang Temple is by far the most visited. Instagram has turned this place into a magnet for everyone visiting Bali.', 'Transfer from Ubud to Seminyak Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Inter Hotel Transfer Ubud Hotel to Seminyak Hotel on Private Basis.', 'Full Day Nusa Penida West Island Tour with Local Lunch on SIC Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A Full day tour to Nusa Penida West Island Tour will give you an experience you will never forget. This is a relatively undeveloped island southeast of the mainland of Bali. Nusa means Island and Penida means priests in Balinese. You won’t find the snazzy beach clubs, organic cafes or trendy restaurants here, but Nusa Penida is still worthy of a visit. It houses some of the most photogenic sights in Bali. In Nusa Penida West Island Tour, we visit 04 Points - Klingking bay, Angel billabong, Broken beach and Crystal Bay.', 'Departure: Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Pick up from the hotel to transfer to the Airport according to the scheduled Flight. * The itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice.']}, 'hashKey': '588591472945f2584fd677200977cf99255b8e24f9965ec1b5eeaeccb71b705d', 'pkgSubtypeId': 4, 'pkgSubtypeName': 'FIT', 'pkgTypeId': 1}
2025-02-03 20:55:49,974 - INFO - ItemOut constructed: id='PKG012462' itinerary_data=savedItineraryData(packageId='PKG012462', packageName='Blissful Bali - Honeymoon Special', days=8, cities=[{'cityName': 'Kuta', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Kuta', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Kuta', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Ubud', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Ubud', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Seminyak', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Seminyak', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Seminyak', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}], highlights=[], pdfName='PKG003958_0_undefined.pdf', price=60458, packageSummary="The 'Blissful Bali - Honeymoon Special' package is an 8-day romantic getaway covering the beautiful island of Bali. This enchanting journey takes you through the vibrant streets of Kuta, the cultural hub of Ubud, and the luxurious resorts of Seminyak, with multiple visits to each destination allowing for a deeper exploration of the island's charms. The itinerary includes a scenic drive through the lush rice fields, a visit to the famous Uluwatu Temple perched on a cliff overlooking the Indian Ocean, a romantic sunset dinner at a beachside restaurant, and a rejuvenating couples' spa treatment at a luxurious resort. You'll also have the opportunity to take a cooking class, learn traditional Balinese dance, and enjoy a leisurely boat ride through the island's picturesque waters.", images=['Kuta.jpeg', 'Bananaboat.jpg', 'Baliswing_new_753.jpeg', 'Bali75309.jpg', 'Gatetheaven7531.jpg', 'Seminyak753.jpg', 'NusaPenida753.jpg', 'Bali_Scenic_7531.jpg'], minimumPrice=60458, thumbnailImage='Bali_Couple_SRP.jpg', packageTheme=['Honeymoon'], packageData="Package ID: PKG012462 is named 'Blissful Bali - Honeymoon Special' and spans 8 days. The itinerary includes:\nDay 1 - Kuta, Meals: N/A, Description: Kuta Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who led you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. It takes about 20 minutes’ drive from airport to your hotel or more depending on the traffic. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 2 - Kuta, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Half Day ATV Quad Bike on Private Basis & Half Day Benoa Beach Tour including Banana Boat on private basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel For a hard core adventurer or a novice, off-roading is the most appealing word & what better than Quad Biking while in Bali. Ride off the beaten track during your Bali vacation on your own All-Terrain Vehicle (ATV). Follow an experienced guide along a challenging track, suitable for all skill levels. One can also enjoy as a co-pilot if you do not want to do it independently. No driving license required & safety is of utmost priority here. Glide past a picturesque landscape of rice fields, bamboo forest, and lush riverside flanked by traditional Balinese villages. It is an ultimate thrill for a couple of hours, you will just want to keep it going. An ideal Bali holiday is incomplete without water sports & what better than the famous Tanjung Benoa beach. This beach best known for its aquatic adventure is located in the Benoa peninsula far away from the hustle & bustle. North of Nusa Dua this beach offers a wide range of water sports from Parasailing to Banana boat ride & so on. Please check with our representatives for all the water sports information. Many shacks & restaurants lined up along the beach make sure that your tummy is full & you enjoy the most., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Kuta, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Half Day Authentic Balinese Massage (60 min) on Private Basis + Bali Swing on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A Bali holiday isn’t complete without an authentic spa experience. Balinese spa treatments are well-known the world over for their healing properties as well as the hospitality by the locals. Refresh your mind, body & soul with a perfect blend of traditional therapeutic remedies & modern day spa rituals. Enjoy this delightful massage & rejuvenate yourself to the core. Swings in Bali are the most trending activities across all social media platforms. And the experiences definitely justify the popularity. Set in Ubud you must try and enjoy this incredible experience. A professional swing guide, will company you to catch the unforgettable memory. Proper set of instructions will guide you through the equipment & safety standards. Soak in the pleasure of being a free bird, reminiscing through your childhood days., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Ubud, Meals: Breakfast and Dinner, Description: Transfer from Kuta to Ubud, Sunset Dinner Cruise on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Inter Hotel Transfer Kuta Hotel to Ubud Hotel on Private Basis No better way than a Sunset Dinner Cruise on a balmy tropical evening. As the daylight fades & the Sun goes into oblivion, you set off on a relaxing short voyage around the alluring Bali harbor & its surrounding areas. Seize the moments, in the cool & calm environs of the top deck aboard the vessel. A plethora of activities will make your evening more memorable. Soak in to the live musical experiences at the bridge deck, savour wide array of delectable international buffet dinner & also witnesses the live Cabaret show. Dance the night away like no one’s watching. Definitely a treat for all age groups but highly recommended for the honeymooners. A remarkable evening well spent on board the Sunset dinner cruise will always give you nostalgia for life., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Ubud, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Full Day Lempuyang Temple Tour on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Ever wondered what its like actually to visit The Gates of Heaven. If you are visiting Bali, then this popular place must be on your list of things to see and do. Most people visit here to get an epic shot between the Candi Bentar â€“ The Gateway. This Candi Bentar is a split gateway seen in almost all Balinese entrances of religious compounds. Usually, these gateways have staircases that lead to its centre point. The two sides represent the Balinese concept of duality and the importance of maintaining a balance between darkness & the bright forces. While you will see Candi Bentars everywhere in Bali, the Gates of Heaven at Lempuyang Temple is by far the most visited. Instagram has turned this place into a magnet for everyone visiting Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 6 - Seminyak, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Transfer from Ubud to Seminyak Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Inter Hotel Transfer Ubud Hotel to Seminyak Hotel on Private Basis., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 7 - Seminyak, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Full Day Nusa Penida West Island Tour with Local Lunch on SIC Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A Full day tour to Nusa Penida West Island Tour will give you an experience you will never forget. This is a relatively undeveloped island southeast of the mainland of Bali. Nusa means Island and Penida means priests in Balinese. You won’t find the snazzy beach clubs, organic cafes or trendy restaurants here, but Nusa Penida is still worthy of a visit. It houses some of the most photogenic sights in Bali. In Nusa Penida West Island Tour, we visit 04 Points - Klingking bay, Angel billabong, Broken beach and Crystal Bay., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 8 - Seminyak, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Departure: Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Pick up from the hotel to transfer to the Airport according to the scheduled Flight. * The itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nThe price is 60458.0. Hotels envisaged include: Overnight stay at the Hotels, Overnight stay at the Hotels, Overnight stay at the Hotels. Meals include: Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included. Inclusions: 03 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar Kuta 02 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar Ubud 02 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar Seminyak Meet & Greet assistance at the Airport Return Airport & Inter Hotel Transfer on Private basis Half Day Benoa Beach Tour including Banana Boat on private basis Half Day ATV Quad Bike on Private Basis (1 Hr Tandem) on private basis Half Day Authentic Balinese Massage (60 min) + Bali Swing on Private Basis Sunset Dinner Cruise on Private Basis Full Day Lempuyang Temple Tour on Private Basis Full Day Nusa Penida West Island Tour with Local Lunch on SIC Basis VAT in Indonesia and all other taxes Daily breakfast, except on Day 1 Meals as mentioned in the itinerary. Travel Insurance (Valid for the age group till 60 Yrs.). Exclusions: TCS & GST Visa Charges Departure PCR test, if applicable All flights services Entrance fees Blackout Dates: 15th Dec 2023 – 05 Jan 2024 Meals not mentioned in the itinerary. Any tips - for guide & Driver Anything not mentioned in the inclusions. Pre & Post tour services & cost Expenditure of a personal nature (Such as uses of Mini – Bar & Refrigerator, laundry service, telephone call, camera fee, tips & Etc.) All drink and beverages Hotel promotional rates not valid during Black out Period / Surcharge Dates / Stop Sales on Hotel Tourism Tax (if applicable) Midnight surcharge The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times.. Product Terms and Conditions: Black Out/Surcharges Dates: 15 Dec 2024 – 05 Jan 2025 The above prices will not be valid for any block out date/ period which is informed during confirmation of the booking; if any change in the price, the same will be applicable for all bookings and to be borne by the customer Terms and Conditions: The upgrade hotel prices are subject to availability at the time of booking. The upgrade hotel prices DO NOT GUARANTEE rooms at the envisaged hotels. The upgrade hotel rooms are subject to availability at the time of booking. For the upgrade hotel, In case the hotel chosen is unavailable we will provide with multiple options of similar category hotel. The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times. The rates are not valid on block out dates. Surcharges as and when applicable will be advised and passengers would be requested to pay the same. Surcharges could be over and above the total package price quoted to the passengers at the time of booking. Guests are requested to check with sales staff before booking their on-wards/connecting flights. The rates are subject to availability of hotel accommodation and sightseeing tours at the time of booking. We reserve the right to use an alternate hotel accommodation of an equal or higher standard. If we source a more expensive alternative, we reserve the right to re-quote based on the higher rates. Prices are not valid during Trade Fair periods. Rates are valid for Indian Passport holders only. International Check in time is 1400 hours / Check out time is 1100 hours, early check in and checkout is subject to availability and cannot be guaranteed. Transfers wherever included are without night surcharges. No refunds either in part or in full will be made for any unutilized service. All the sightseeing tours and excursions are organized by local companies. The timings and days of operation are subject to alteration. Changes if any will be intimated at the time of booking. Sightseeing’s tours are strictly based on whether conditions and also local service providers have rights to cancel the sightseeing tours without prior notice. Rates subject to change without prior notice and also for clients traveling during weekends. Offer if any can be withdrawn at any point without prior notice. Bookings once confirmed are subject to cancellation charges which shall be