2025-02-03 20:55:49,980 - INFO - Elasticsearch response: {'took': 2, 'timed_out': False, '_shards': {'total': 1, 'successful': 1, 'skipped': 0, 'failed': 0}, 'hits': {'total': {'value': 1, 'relation': 'eq'}, 'max_score': 6.6995, 'hits': [{'_index': 'tcildatav1', '_id': 'PKG012907', '_score': 6.6995, '_source': {'packageId': 'PKG012907', 'packageName': 'Bali - Buy 1 Get 1 Free', 'packageTheme': ['Family', 'Couple Special'], 'days': 5, 'cities': [{'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Bali', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}], 'highlights': [], 'pdfName': 'PKG012907_0_20250203121507.pdf', 'price': 18367.0, 'minimumPrice': 18367.0, 'packageData': "Package ID: PKG012907 is named 'Bali - Buy 1 Get 1 Free' and spans 5 days. The itinerary includes:\nDay 1 - Bali, Meals: N/A, Description: Arrive at Bali (PVT basis) Welcome to Bali – Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who led you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. It takes about 20 minutes’ drive from airport to your hotel or more depending on the traffic. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up. Overnight stay at Kuta., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 2 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Full Day Kintamani Hot Spring & Ubud village Tour (PVT Basis) Visit Kintamani Hot Spring Kintamani Hot Spring features eight natural hot spring pools and one warm olympic sized pool. Heated deep within the earth, minerals from the colorless and odorless hot spring brings healing and curative powers. Enjoy a relaxing dip with the majestic panorama! *Inclusions: Natural Hot Spring Pools, Toya Water Slide with Tubes, Towel & Locker, Change & Shower Room, Facility Visit Ubud Coffee Plantation Bali Coffee Plantation is a green garden for cultivating coffee from various types of coffee in the world. You can find the various of coffee plantation in this garden. In fact, you can also find other plants such as cocoa, coconut or other tropical plants such as medicinal plants or herbs. Furthermore, Indonesia is one of the best coffee producing countries. Even, the annual production of 600 thousand tons can supply seven percent of the world’s coffee needs. There are different things that you will find at Bali Coffee Plantations, namely Luwak Coffee. This type of coffee is very well known as well as the most expensive coffee in the world. This coffee comes from civet droppings that have been processed in such a way. Continue to visit Ubud Royal Palace Puri Saren Ubud or more popular name as a Bali Ubud Royal Palace is an Ubud Kingdom Palace with Beautiful Balinese traditional houses of residence of Ubud King. It is set in the center of Ubud Bali with traditional art market just in front of it and it is found by IDA Tjokorda Putu Kandel who has commanded from Year 1800 – 1823. If time permits, we can drop by Ubud Art Market. The Ubud Art Market is a great place to find beautiful silk scarves, lightweight shirts, statues, kites, handmade woven bags, baskets or hats and many other hand – crafted goods. Locally known as Pasar Seni Ubud, the market is opposite the Puri Saren Royal Ubud Palace and opens daily., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa Beach with Uluwatu Temple Tour Followed with Kecak Dance. (PVT Basis) Enjoy Breakfast in Hotel. Salty Air! Sandy Hair! Feel the tropical breeze and get closer to Indian Ocean with our selected Water Sports Activity. Pick up for Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa Beach (Incl. 1 x Jet Ski – Banana Boat Ride) and Complimentary 1 x Parasailing or Flying Fish. Later proceed Uluwatu Temple sits on 70-meter-high cliff protruding above Indonesian Ocean. The main site of Uluwatu Tours is visiting this temple. There are hundreds of monkeys roaming along the path outside temple. A small forest lies at the front and hundreds of monkey’s dwells here. They are believed to guard the temple from bad influence. The Serpentine pathway to the temple is fortified by concrete walls on the cliff sides. When sun goes down, we will witness the Theatrical Fire Dance Show ‘Kecak Fire Dance’. Kecak dance is that the accompanying music is provided by the human voice, the gamelan suara, a choir of a hundred men or more sitting in concentric circle, swaying, standing up, lying prone as the story develops. Amongst the swaying masses the voices of the storytellers can be heard telling the unfolding tale. The music generated from a combination sounds of members cak which were about 50 – 70 people all of them will make music in acapella., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast and Local Lunch, Description: Day free for Leisure Morning Breakfast at the Hotel. Rest Day Free for Leisure to explore the Bali., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Bali, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Depart from Kuta Morning after breakfast; you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back home to India. * The above itinerary is tentative and subject to change without prior notice. EXTENSION NIGHTS KUTA: Travel Validity: 01 Oct – 20 Dec 2024 & 07 Jan – 31 Mar 2025 CATEGORY HOTELS PACKAGE COST: PER PERSON IN USD SINGLE TWIN /DOUBLE TRIPLE CHILDWITH BED CHILD NO BED STANDARD Hotel Siesta Legian (Superior Room) or similar NA 32 NA NA NA VALUE Antanya Hotel Kuta (Deluxe Room) /Solia Legian Bali (Solia Deluxe) Or Similar NA 50 NA NA NA, GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nThe price is 18367.0. Hotels envisaged include: Overnight stay at the Hotels, Accomodation from Jan to March 2024\n\n02 night’s accommodation at Aryaduta or Similar in Bali\n02 night’s accommodation at The Seiryu Boutique Villas Seminyak or Similar in\xa0Villa\n\nAccomodation from April to Sept 2024\n\n02 night’s accommodation at Kuta Paradiso or Similar in Bali\n02 night’s accommodation at The Seiryu Boutique Villas Seminyak or Similar in\xa0Villa\n, Accomodation from Jan to March 2024\n\n02 night’s accommodation at \xa0Solia Legian or Similar in Bali\n02 night’s accommodation at \xa0Maharaja Villas Seminyak or Similar in\xa0Villa\n\nAccomodation from April to Sept 2024\n\n02 night’s accommodation at \xa0Solia Legian or Similar in Bali\n02 night’s accommodation at \xa0Grand Kesambi Resort & Villa or Similar in\xa0Villa\n. Meals include: Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included. Inclusions: 04 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar in Kuta. Daily breakfast, except on Day 1 Airport / hotel / airport transfers on (PVT Basis) Meet & Greet assistance at the airport English Speaking Driver during Transfer & Tour Full Day Kintamani Hot Spring & Ubud village Tour (PVT Basis) Water Sports at Tanjung Benoa Beach with Uluwatu Temple Tour Followed with Kecak Dance. (PVT Basis) Complimentary Welcome drink upon arrival at the Hotel & Villa Complimentary Balinese Sarong per person (adult only) as welcome gift on arrival (Adult only) Complimentary 01 bottle of Mineral Water per person on arrival Free Wi-Fi at Hotel/Villa/ Resort area Travel Insurance (Valid for the age group till 60 Yrs.). Exclusions: TCS & GST Departure PCR test, if applicable All flights service Meals not mentioned in the itinerary. Any tips for guide & Driver Anything not mentioned in the inclusions. Pre & Post tour services & cost Expenditure of a personal nature (Such as uses of Mini – Bar & Refrigerator, laundry service, telephone call, camera fee, tips & Etc) All drink and beverages Hotel promotional rates not valid during Black out Period / Surcharge Dates / Stop Sales on Hotel Tourism Tax (if applicable) Midnight surcharge Black Out Dates Surcharge - 15-Dec-2024 to 6-Jan-2025 New Year and Christmas // 26 Jan – 02 Feb 2025 Chinese New Year // 28 Mar – 03 Apr 2025 Nyepi Day The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times.. Product Terms and Conditions: During Peak Season: Minimum 2 Nights Stay is required No Check Out period on 31 December 2024 and 01 January 2025 Nyepi Day (Silent Day) is on 29 March 2025. No outdoor activity is allowed, and Airport will be closed from 05.59 am 29 March 2025 to 06.00 am 30 March 2025 Compulsory New Year Dinner will be Applicable according to the Resort The rates are not valid on block out dates. Surcharges as and when applicable will be advised and passengers would be requested to pay the same Surcharges could be over and above the total package price quoted to the passengers at the time of booking. Guests are requested to check with sales staff before booking their on-wards/connecting flights. The rates are subject to availability of hotel accommodation and sightseeing tours at the time of booking. We reserve the right to use an alternate hotel accommodation of an equal or higher standard. If we source a more expensive alternative, we reserve the right to re-quote based on the higher rates. Prices are not valid during Trade Fair periods. Rates are valid for Indian Passport holders only. International Check in time is 1400 hours / Check out time is 1100 hours, early check in and checkout is subject to availability and cannot be guaranteed. Transfers wherever included are without night surcharges. No refunds either in part or in full will be made for any unutilized service. All the sightseeing tours and excursions are organized by local companies. The timings and days of operation are subject to alteration. Changes if any will be intimated at the time of booking. Sightseeing’s tours are strictly based on whether conditions and also local service providers have rights to cancel the sightseeing tours without prior notice. Rates subject to change without prior notice and also for clients traveling during weekends. Offer if any can be withdrawn at any point without prior notice. Bookings once confirmed are subject to cancellation charges which shall be advised at that time. TCIL is not responsible for any change in the price due to factors not in the control of the organization. As a practice all international hotels charge a security deposit via credit card or cash, at the time of check- in for each room. The amount will vary according to the hotel and is refunded back to the clients upon check-out. Debit cards should not be offered as it will be charged immediately and refunded only after 2-3 weeks. If any additional services or mini bar or any other service is utilized at the hotel, the hotel reserves the right to charge the same on this security deposit provided by the client. TCIL would not be responsible for these transactions and these are solely between the hotels and the clients.. Highlights of the package: .", 'packageSummary': 'The \'Bali - Buy 1 Get 1 Free\' package is a 5-day tour that takes you on an unforgettable journey through the beautiful island of Bali. You\'ll spend your days exploring the stunning landscapes and vibrant culture of this Indonesian paradise, with visits to iconic temples like Tanah Lot and Uluwatu, as well as scenic stops at Kuta Beach and Seminyak. The itinerary also includes a relaxing day at the famous Tirta Empul Temple water gardens, where you can rejuvenate your spirit in the sacred springs. Additionally, you\'ll have the opportunity to take part in a traditional Balinese dance performance, learn about local cuisine with a cooking class, and enjoy a sunset dinner cruise along the coast. With its unbeatable value proposition of "buy one get one free", this package is an absolute steal for anyone looking to experience the best of Bali without breaking the bank!', 'thumbnailImage': 'Bali_Temple_267.jpg', 'images': ['53700_Ulun_Danu_Batur_temple_Bali_Indonesia_753.jpg', 'Kintamani.jpg', 'BaliAdventure.jpg', 'Bali_Sunset_753.jpg', '16882_Roofs_in_Pura_Besakih_Temple_Ba