2025-02-03 20:55:49,994 - INFO - Elasticsearch response: {'took': 1, 'timed_out': False, '_shards': {'total': 1, 'successful': 1, 'skipped': 0, 'failed': 0}, 'hits': {'total': {'value': 1, 'relation': 'eq'}, 'max_score': 6.6995, 'hits': [{'_index': 'tcildatav1', '_id': 'PKG012548', '_score': 6.6995, '_source': {'packageId': 'PKG012548', 'packageName': 'Discover Bali', 'packageTheme': ['Honeymoon'], 'days': 7, 'cities': [{'cityName': 'Kuta', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Kuta', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Kuta', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Gili', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Ubud', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Ubud', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}, {'cityName': 'Ubud', 'geoLocation': {'lat': 0.0, 'lon': 0.0}}], 'highlights': [], 'pdfName': 'PKG009597_0_undefined.pdf', 'price': 55082.0, 'minimumPrice': 55082.0, 'packageData': "Package ID: PKG012548 is named 'Discover Bali' and spans 7 days. The itinerary includes:\nDay 1 - Kuta, Meals: N/A, Description: Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who lead you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. It takes about 20 minutes’ drive from airport to your hotel or more depending on the traffic. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 2 - Kuta, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Half Day Benoa Beach Tour including Banana Boat on private basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel An ideal Bali holiday is incomplete without water sports & what better than the famous Tanjung Benoa beach. This beach best known for its aquatic adventure is located in the Benoa peninsula far away from the hustle & bustle. North of Nusa Dua this beach offers a wide range of water sports from Parasailing to Banana boat ride & so on. Please check with our representatives for all the water sports information. Many shacks & restaurants lined up along the beach make sure that your tummy is full & you enjoy the most., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 3 - Kuta, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Full Day Kintamani Volcano Tour with Ubud Village on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A visit to Kintamani Volcano is a rare opportunity to experience one of Bali’s last remaining active volcanos up close. This is one of the most popular and best day trip in Bali. The tour begins with the sights of a vibrant art village. Here you can meet with the people who keep the techniques of the regions handicrafts alive with a stop at Tohpati village, widely known as the centre of handmade Balinese Batik weaving. Next stop is Celuk village famous for producing high-grade gold and silver handicrafts. Continue trip to Mas Village, one of the many artists villages surrounding Ubud, is the best place on the island to find high-quality Balinese woodcarvings, considered some of the best woodcarvings in the world. The tour continues to the Mount & Lake Batur in Kintamani village for some stunning views of the beautiful locales in this region. This tour only cover viewing Mount Batur Volcano from viewpoint only. Your tour ends in one of the most famous coffee plantations in the area. Here you can look & taste many kinds of coffees from Indonesia., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 4 - Gili, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Transfer from Kuta to Gili Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Seminyak Hotel to Gili Hotel by Fast boat + Cidomo (Horse Cart), GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 5 - Ubud, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Transfer from Gili to Ubud Gili Hotel to Ubud Hotel by Fast boat + Cidomo (Horse Cart), GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 6 - Ubud, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Full Day Nusa Penida with Local Lunch on SIC Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A Full day tour to Nusa Penida West Island Tour will give you an experience you will never forget. This is a relatively undeveloped island southeast of the mainland of Bali. Nusa means Island and Penida means priests in Balinese. You won’t find the snazzy beach clubs, organic cafes or trendy restaurants here, but Nusa Penida is still worthy of a visit. It houses some of the most photogenic sights in Bali. In Nusa Penida West Island Tour, we visit 04 Points - Klingking bay, Angel billabong, Broken beach and Crystal Bay., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nDay 7 - Ubud, Meals: Breakfast, Description: Departure Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Pick up from the hotel to transfer to the Airport according to the scheduled Flight. * The itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice., GeoLocation: (Lat: 0.0, Lon: 0.0).\nThe price is 55082.0. Hotels envisaged include: Overnight stay at the Hotels, Overnight stay at the Hotels, Overnight stay at the Hotels. Meals include: Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included, Breakfast Included. Inclusions: 03 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar Kuta 01 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar Gili 02 nights stay at the selected hotel option or similar Ubud Meet & Greet assistance at the Airport Return Airport & Inter Hotel Transfer on Private basis Return Transfer to Gili by Fast Boat + Cidomo on SIC basis Half Day Benoa Beach Tour including Banana Boat on private basis Full Day Kintamani Volcano Tour with Ubud Village on Private Basis Full Day Nusa Penida with Local Lunch on SIC Basis VAT in Indonesia and all other taxes Daily breakfast, except on Day 1 Meals as mentioned in the itinerary. Travel Insurance (Valid Till the age of 60 yrs.). Exclusions: TCS & GST Visa Charges Departure PCR test, if applicable All flights services Entrance fees Blackout Dates: 15th December 2024 – 05th Jan 2025 Meals not mentioned in the itinerary. Any tips - for guide & Driver Anything not mentioned in the inclusions. Pre & Post tour services & cost Expenditure of a personal nature (Such as uses of Mini – Bar & Refrigerator, laundry service, telephone call, camera fee, tips & Etc.) All drink and beverages Hotel promotional rates not valid during Black out Period / Surcharge Dates / Stop Sales on Hotel Tourism Tax (if applicable) Midnight surcharge The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times. The prices will not be valid for any block out date/ period which is informed during confirmation of the booking; if any change in the price, the same will be applicable for all bookings and to be borne by the customer.. Product Terms and Conditions: Terms and Conditions: The prices will not be valid for any block out date/ period which is informed during confirmation of the booking; if any change in the price, the same will be applicable for all bookings and to be borne by the customer. The upgrade hotel prices are subject to availability at the time of booking. The upgrade hotel prices DO NOT GUARANTEE rooms at the envisaged hotels. The upgrade hotel rooms are subject to availability at the time of booking. For the upgrade hotel, In case the hotel chosen is unavailable we will provide with multiple options of similar category hotel. The rates are valid for minimum 02 adults travelling together at all times. The rates are not valid on block out dates. Surcharges as and when applicable will be advised and passengers would be requested to pay the same. Surcharges could be over and above the total package price quoted to the passengers at the time of booking. Guests are requested to check with sales staff before booking their on-wards/connecting flights. The rates are subject to availability of hotel accommodation and sightseeing tours at the time of booking. We reserve the right to use an alternate hotel accommodation of an equal or higher standard. If we source a more expensive alternative, we reserve the right to re-quote based on the higher rates. Prices are not valid during Trade Fair periods. Rates are valid for Indian Passport holders only. International Check in time is 1400 hours / Check out time is 1100 hours, early check in and checkout is subject to availability and cannot be guaranteed. Transfers wherever included are without night surcharges. No refunds either in part or in full will be made for any unutilized service. All the sightseeing tours and excursions are organized by local companies. The timings and days of operation are subject to alteration. Changes if any will be intimated at the time of booking. Sightseeing’s tours are strictly based on whether conditions and also local service providers have rights to cancel the sightseeing tours without prior notice. Rates subject to change without prior notice and also for clients traveling during weekends. Offer if any can be withdrawn at any point without prior notice. Bookings once confirmed are subject to cancellation charges which shall be advised at that time. TC is not responsible for any change in the price due to factors not in the control of the organization. As a practice all international hotels charge a security deposit via credit card or cash, at the time of check- in for each room. The amount will vary according to the hotel and is refunded back to the clients upon check-out. Debit cards should not be offered as it will be charged immediately and refunded only after 2-3 weeks. If any additional services or mini bar or any other service is utilized at the hotel, the hotel reserves the right to charge the same on this security deposit provided by the client. TC would not be responsible for these transactions and these are solely between the hotels and the clients.. Highlights of the package: .", 'packageSummary': "The 'Discover Bali' package is a 7-day tour that takes you to the beautiful island of Bali, covering the vibrant city of Kuta and the cultural hub of Ubud multiple times. During this journey, you will have the opportunity to explore the stunning landscapes, temples, and markets of Bali, with visits to iconic sites such as Uluwatu Temple, Tirta Empul Temple, and the famous Monkey Forest in Ubud. You'll also get to experience the island's rich culture through traditional dance performances and cooking classes, and enjoy some relaxation time on the stunning beaches of Kuta and Gili Islands. The package includes guided tours, water sports activities, and a chance to explore the local markets and try the delicious Balinese cuisine.", 'thumbnailImage': 'DiscoverBali2671.jpg', 'images': ['Bali1.jpg', 'BannanaBoat.jpg', 'MountBatur753.jpg', 'Bali12.jpg', 'TanahLotTemple75345.jpg', 'NusaPenida753.jpg', 'Bali75390.jpg'], 'visitingCountries': ['Indonesia'], 'departureCities': ['Jammu', 'Dehra Dun', 'Surat', 'Patna', 'Chennai', 'Aurangabad', 'Indore', 'Bangalore', 'Mangalore', 'Amritsar', 'Chandigarh', 'Kozhikode', 'Hyderabad', 'Delhi', 'Raipur', 'Bhubaneswar', 'Ahmedabad', 'Vadodara', 'Madurai', 'Chandigarh', 'Lucknow', 'Coimbatore', 'Kanpur', 'Vadodara', 'Kochi', 'Visakhapatnam', 'Nagpur', 'Varanasi', 'Guwahati', 'Dehra Dun', 'Mumbai', 'Bhopal', 'Bhubaneswar', 'Jaipur', 'Bhopal'], 'packageItinerary': {'summary': "The 'Discover Bali' package is a 7-day tour that takes you to the beautiful island of Bali, covering the vibrant city of Kuta and the cultural hub of Ubud multiple times. During this journey, you will have the opportunity to explore the stunning landscapes, temples, and markets of Bali, with visits to iconic sites such as Uluwatu Temple, Tirta Empul Temple, and the famous Monkey Forest in Ubud. You'll also get to experience the island's rich culture through traditional dance performances and cooking classes, and enjoy some relaxation time on the stunning beaches of Kuta and Gili Islands. The package includes guided tours, water sports activities, and a chance to explore the local markets and try the delicious Balinese cuisine.", 'itinerary': ['Arrival at the Ngurah Rai, Bali International Airport, meet & greet by our local guide who lead you to the parking area to board on vehicle for your transfer to your hotel. It takes about 20 minutes’ drive from airport to your hotel or more depending on the traffic. Upon arrival at the hotel, directly check in and freshen up.', 'Half Day Benoa Beach Tour including Banana Boat on private basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel An ideal Bali holiday is incomplete without water sports & what better than the famous Tanjung Benoa beach. This beach best known for its aquatic adventure is located in the Benoa peninsula far away from the hustle & bustle. North of Nusa Dua this beach offers a wide range of water sports from Parasailing to Banana boat ride & so on. Please check with our representatives for all the water sports information. Many shacks & restaurants lined up along the beach make sure that your tummy is full & you enjoy the most.', 'Full Day Kintamani Volcano Tour with Ubud Village on Private Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A visit to Kintamani Volcano is a rare opportunity to experience one of Bali’s last remaining active volcanos up close. This is one of the most popular and best day trip in Bali. The tour begins with the sights of a vibrant art village. Here you can meet with the people who keep the techniques of the regions handicrafts alive with a stop at Tohpati village, widely known as the centre of handmade Balinese Batik weaving. Next stop is Celuk village famous for producing high-grade gold and silver handicrafts. Continue trip to Mas Village, one of the many artists villages surrounding Ubud, is the best place on the island to find high-quality Balinese woodcarvings, considered some of the best woodcarvings in the world. The tour continues to the Mount & Lake Batur in Kintamani village for some stunning views of the beautiful locales in this region. This tour only cover viewing Mount Batur Volcano from viewpoint only. Your tour ends in one of the most famous coffee plantations in the area. Here you can look & taste many kinds of coffees from Indonesia.', 'Transfer from Kuta to Gili Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Seminyak Hotel to Gili Hotel by Fast boat + Cidomo (Horse Cart)', 'Transfer from Gili to Ubud Gili Hotel to Ubud Hotel by Fast boat + Cidomo (Horse Cart)', 'Full Day Nusa Penida with Local Lunch on SIC Basis Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel A Full day tour to Nusa Penida West Island Tour will give you an experience you will never forget. This is a relatively undeveloped island southeast of the mainland of Bali. Nusa means Island and Penida means priests in Balinese. You won’t find the snazzy beach clubs, organic cafes or trendy restaurants here, but Nusa Penida is still worthy of a visit. It houses some of the most photogenic sights in Bali. In Nusa Penida West Island Tour, we visit 04 Points - Klingking bay, Angel billabong, Broken beach and Crystal Bay.', 'Departure Enjoy Breakfast at the Hotel Pick up from the hotel to transfer to the Airport according to the scheduled Flight. * The itinerary is tentative and subjected to change without prior notice.']}, 'hashKey': 'c4ba87b098ed5c9ffb78886204d19ad269845e9a1f32a9dce4119c20378ac84f', 'pkgSubtypeId': 4, 'pkgSubtypeName': 'FIT', 'pkgTypeId': 1}}]}}
